title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and crush into small pieces.
Soften cream cheese with mayonnaise and add to shrimp.
Add eggs and onion.
Chill for a couple of hours.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: barbecued chili steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except beef.
Slash fat edges of meat. Place in shallow dish.
Pour vinegar catsup mixture over steak. Let
stand
3 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator,
turning
steak
several
times.
Drain
steak, reserving
marinade.
Pat
dry with paper towel.
Cook over hot coals about
20 minutes on each side for rare.
Cook 25 minutes on each
side
for
medium.
Brush
occasionally with reserved marinade.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla and dash of salt until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Fold in coconut. Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in 325° oven about 20 minutes. Cool. Makes 20 to 24.

title: baked stuffed double fudge brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk; set aside.
Pour chopped walnuts, chocolate chips and caramel mix on top of brownies. Spread remaining batter on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
It spreads easier if you spoon small amounts on and bake for 5 minutes.
Then remove from oven and spread evenly.
Return for final baking.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: hot pepper and wieners
directions: Put wieners in large pan and cover with cold water.
Bring to boil (do not let boil).
Remove from heat and put lid on pan.
Let set while preparing the canning mixture.
Mix other ingredients together and bring to a rolling boil.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts in a low oven in a jelly roll pan for about 5 minutes.
Fold sugar and salt into egg whites, while beating and whip to a stiff meringue.
Fold nuts into meringue.
Melt margarine in jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) in 325° oven.
Spread nut mixture over margarine, separating nuts as much as possible. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn nuts over with a spatula every 8 minutes.
They are ready when covering is light brown and no margarine remains in pan.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Bone and grind all the meats and put in large heavy metal pot. Cut corn off the cobs and add corn, okra and tomatoes to meat mixture.
Put the lemon slices and the juice in the pot and stir well.
Cook slowly over low heat for 24 hours, adding salt and peppers to taste.
Hot sauce may be added if desired.
Some folks like a dash of sugar.
Serves a bunch!

title: chicken strata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place buttered bread in bottom of square baking dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and spread on top of bread.
Combine chicken soup, milk and egg and pour over bread. Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with croutons and cheese 10 minutes before it's done.

title: the best coconut cake
directions: Cook sugar and water 10 minutes. Add the flavoring.
Pour mixture over baked cake while it is still warm.
Let set until cool and turn out on cake plate. Frost with 7-Minute Frosting and sprinkle with coconut.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter, mix in pretzels and sugar.
Spread on cookie sheet and brown at 400 degrees for 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix pineapple and cream cheese/sugar blend.
Fold in cool whip.
Add pretzel mixture just before serving.

title: snowball surprise cookies
directions: Put softened butter into a bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla. Blend well with a spoon until creamy.
Pour flour into butter mixture and blend.
Pinch off dough and roll with hands into 1-inch snowballs.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for about 40 minutes or until brown.
While snowballs are still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 15 snowballs.

title: apple and oat bran muffins
directions: In medium bowl, stir flour, oat bran, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In small bowl, combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Stir in apple.
Store batter in refrigerator tightly covered for up to 5 days.
Spray muffin pans. Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Yields 12.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt margarine. Add carrot, onion, potato, garlic and bay leave and thyme. Tossing to coat with margarine. Stir in half cup chicken broth. Cover and cook 15 minutes. Raise heat to moderate, stirring in remaining two cups broth and milk. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf. Add remaining broth, salt and pepper. Cook 3 more minutes.

title: apricot chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 minutes or until set.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and milk.
Blend.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add cubed toast.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Place casserole in pan of water (warm) and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute first 6 ingredients.
When sauteed, add shrimp and tomatoes.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Cook additional 5 minutes.
Soak slice of bread in water and squeeze all water out.
Add to mixture along with 2 cups cooked rice and 1/4 cup chopped parsley.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 1/2 hour at 450°.

title: eggplant stew
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Add other ingredients, seasoning to taste.
Simmer until eggplant is tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve with rice and salad.

title: tempura batter no. 1
directions: Mix ingredients into batter and dip whatever you like; such as vegetables, onion rings, squash cut French fry style, mushrooms, shrimp, etc. into batter, letting excess drop off. Cook in deep hot fat (350° to 365°) until tender and browned. Drain on paper towel and serve warm.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Test doneness when toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, brown sugar, mustard, catsup and dry onions in oven-safe casserole dish.
Microwave bacon until done crisply. Break up bacon and crumble into bean mixture, mixing well. Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes before you're ready to eat, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; mix well. Add zucchini and mix.
Blend dry ingredients, then add to mixture.
Add walnuts.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fudge frosting(no sugar)
directions: In saucepan, mix fructose, milk and cornstarch together until cornstarch "completely" dissolves.
Add broken chocolate and cook over medium heat until chocolate melts and mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir until creamy. Cool and spread over cake (Sweet 'N Low cake mix at Kroger or your own sugar-free cake recipe; one layer).

title: shrimp dip
directions: I chop everything separately in a food processor and put in a bowl.
I blend cream cheese in the food processor and add to the bowl.
You can either mix by hand or use an electric hand mixer. Put in serving bowl and chill.
Better if done the night before so all flavors can blend.
Serve with crackers.

title: casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in bowl, next 8 ingredients. Add yeast mix.
Start adding flour (at first with mixer) until all flour is added.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down dough.
Put into well-buttered 8-inch round (1 1/2 to 2 quart) casserole dish.
Let rise in warm place for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
While still warm, brush with soft butter and sprinkle with sea salt.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat, eggs and bread crumbs and shape into small balls.
(Mixture will be firm.)
Bake at 425 degrees about 10-15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Simmer sliced potatoes about 20 minutes; drain.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in pie crusts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Make sure it is cooked in the middle.

title: potato crocketts
directions: Mix soup, potatoes and parsley.
Roll mixture into balls. Roll balls in bread crumbs, then dip them into the beaten egg and dip them in bread crumbs again.
Deep fat fry until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix.
Fold in 1 tub of Cool Whip.
Pour over all.
Sprinkle a few finely chopped nuts on top.
Dream Whip may be used instead of Cool Whip.

title: cherry upside-down cake
directions: Drain juice from cherries; set aside.
Add 1 cup sugar to cherries and put in greased baking dish 9-inch square.
Put oil in measuring cup; add egg and enough milk to make 1 cup.
Mix with 1 cup sugar and dry ingredients.
Pour over cherries in pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef; drain and cool.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add nacho chips, crushed up in salad, just before serving so chips don't get soggy.
Delicious.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add peanut butter and well beaten egg.
Sift other ingredients and work into mixture.
If dry, add a little cold water.
Work into a smooth roll.
Wrap in wax paper. Chill in refrigerator.

title: fish fillets with orange sauce
directions: Broil fish with salt, pepper and paprika until it flakes with a fork.
Combine rest of ingredients to make Orange Sauce.
Serve over fish.
Add orange slices and parsley for garnish.

title: powdered sugar icing
directions: Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and 1 tablespoon milk.
Stir in milk 1 tablespoon at a time until of drizzling consistency.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and 1 or 2 tablespoons flour over apples.
Place in a pan.
Mix other ingredients and sprinkle over other mixture.
Bake it at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients; pour salt on the mixture.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain and throw juice away.
In a large pot combine vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Turn onto low heat and stir in celery seed and turmeric.
Let this come to a boil; put into jars and seal.

title: red waldorf astoria cake
directions: Mix vinegar with soda.
Mix a paste of 1 ounce red food coloring and cocoa (add enough water to make 1/4 cup).
Cream Spry, sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Add cocoa paste.
Add vanilla, flour and the salt with the buttermilk.
Add vinegar and soda.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low country boil
directions: Ingredients
are
measured
for each person. In a large pot, boil
potatoes.
When
they
are
almost done, add corn, onion and sausage.
When this is almost done, add crab.
When crab turn red, add shrimp until pink.
Taste for doneness.
Do not overcook.
When
ready to serve, put all ingredients onto large platter or table and let everyone help themselves.

title: baked vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables; drain well and put in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables; cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Arrange in casserole or pan (up to 9 x 13-inch) the sliced peaches.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2/3 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine or butter.

title: chocolate fanny farmer bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and salt; cool.
In large bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Beat in cocoa mix.
Add flour and vanilla. Spread in greased pan and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and put marshmallows on top.
Melt and cool.

title: zucchini soup a la kenitha
directions: Slowly saute onion in margarine until soft, but not brown.
Add 3 cups of water and 3 bouilon cubes.
Bring to a boil and add zucchini.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and paprika.
Cook gently until tender.
Place mixture in blender and blend until slightly thick.

title: grandma's smothered chicken
directions: Heat oil in deep 12-inch skillet over low heat 5 minutes. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place in hot skillet.
Cover chicken with yellow and green onions.
Cook chicken over medium heat 10 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Reduce heat to low; cook 5 minutes.
Turn.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Place in large pot or Dutch oven.
Set aside.
Continue heating skillet over low heat.
Stir together flour, soy sauce, 2 cups hot water and onion powder in medium bowl with fork or whisk.
Cook flour mixture in hot skillet, stirring constantly until boils and thickens.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Pour over chicken and simmer over low heat 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables and combine; add celery and green peppers.
Mix together marinade of sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: apple-cranberry sweet potatoes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine pie filling, cranberry sauce and marmalade.
Gently stir in sweet potatoes.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: brownies
directions: Bake Duncan Hines brownies as directed. When cool, cover with a cherry pie filling and cover with a medium size Cool Whip or whipping cream.
Enjoy!

title: baked tuna patties
directions: In a saucepan, cook celery in 3 tablespoons of butter until tender. Stir in flour, paprika and salt. Stir in milk; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cool slightly. Drain and flake tuna. Mix into sauce with bread crumbs and onions. Form into 8 (2 1/2-inch) patties. Beat egg with 1 tablespoon water. Dip patties into egg and then crackers. Place in lightly greased baking pan. Melt remaining butter and drizzle over patties. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden. Serves 4.

title: squash pie
directions: Blend squash, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs and milk, beating until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Serve cold.

title: turtle cake
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Grease pan, no flour.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour 1/2 the batter into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onions and bell peppers. Combine ground beef with onions and peppers in large pan and mix. Add spaghetti sauce and mix well.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cook vermicelli according to package directions and drain.
Mix vermicelli with spaghetti sauce and pour into large casserole dish.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake in oven at 300° for approximately 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Roll ground beef into balls and brown.
Drain off excess fat. Simmer meatballs together with jelly and chili sauce for about 1 hour.
Note: Use equal amounts of jelly and chili sauce.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Place in casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Pour soup over the mixture and bake for 30 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make jello; refrigerate.
When cake is cool, poke holes in it (handle of wooden spoon works well).
When jello starts to jell, pour on and into holes of cake.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Make pudding.
Pour over cake.
Let stand 1 hour.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Keep refrigerated.
If cake doesn't set between layers, pudding and Cool Whip will slip off.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix flour, Cheddar cheese, baking powder and salt, then beat eggs and milk and add to dry ingredients slowly.
Fold in melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in loaf pan.

title: macdonald's special sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use for hamburgers or hot dogs.

title: chocolate fudge cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare chocolate crumb crust.
Crust: Combine 1 1/2 cups vanilla wafer crumbs (about 45 wafers), 6 tablespoons confectioners sugar, 1/3 cup unsweetened cocoa and 1/3 cup margarine or butter (melted).
Press firmly on bottom and 1/2-inch up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: stir-fried shrimp har lok
directions: In wok or medium saucepan and over high flame, heat oil and salt.
Brown onion.
Add green pepper and toss several times.
Add shrimp and toss several times.
Pour in ketchup.
Stir and cover for a minute.
Stir once more and pour over cooked rice.
Serve immediately (for 2 persons).

title: vegetable beef surprise
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook noodles.
Mix all ingredients.
Then in casserole dish layer mixed ingredients and then a layer of cheese until mixture is used.
Make final layer of cheese.
Bake at 300° until all cheese is melted, approximately 20 minutes.

title: jamaican dark christmas fruit cake(yields 2 tube cakes, 6 pounds each)
directions: Soak the raisins and currants in the liquor for 1 hour.
Cut the dates, peels, pineapple and citron into paper-thin strips. Combine with the nuts.
Sprinkle with one cup of the flour; mix well.
To the remaining flour add the spices and soda.
Gradually add the sugar to the butter in a mixing bowl.
Cream well.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Add the sifted dry ingredients alternately with the combined juice, extract and soaked raisins. Blend in the fruits and nuts.
Pack the batter into two oiled and paper-lined tube pans (9-inch), filling them two-thirds full.
Bake in a very slow oven until a cake tester comes away clean.
Invert upon a cake rack.
Do not remove the paper.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and stir well.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When cool, top with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: quiche
directions: Saute together the oil, water and onion, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour tofu mixture into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes, until set.

title: edible dirt
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in food processor.
Set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar in small bowl. In a third bowl, whip together pudding and milk at lowest mixer speed for 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese mixture to pudding; then fold in Cool
Whip.
Stir by hand until mixture is uniform in color.
Alternate layers of Oreos and creamed mixture in flower pot, starting and ending with with Oreo crumbs.
Decorate with gummy worms.
Cover pot with foil and refrigerate for 24 hrs.

title: georgie's brownies
directions: Mix
ingredients
with wooden spoon (don't use electric mixer).
Bake
25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Grease only sides of baking pan.

title: pecan squares
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together flour, sugar, butter and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly and evenly into a greased 15 inch x 10 inch x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, in another bowl, combine first five filling ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Spread evenly over hot crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until set. Cool on a wire rack.

title: betty croome's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
The longer it cooks, the better.

title: snickerdoodles(favorite cinnamon cookies)
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add 2 cups sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture; beat until well combined.

title: california casserole
directions: In a large skillet, combine ground beef, garlic, salt, pepper, sugar, tomato sauce and paste.
Bring to a boil, stirring to break up meat.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles.
Drain and toss with butter.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, onions and olives.
Spoon about 1 cup meat mix in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread noodles evenly on top.
Cover noodles with rest of meat mixture.
Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion in	hot fat.
Add meat and salt and pepper; brown. Add
drained
beans and soup; pour into greased casserole dish. Mash
potatoes;
add
milk,
egg and seasonings to potatoes. Spoon
in
mounds over meat.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the last 3; mix well. Pour in an 8 x 8 or quart casserole dish. Mix bread crumbs, crushed shoestring potatoes and grated cheese; sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. burn's apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour and apples.
Add flour and stir, then add apples.
Vegetable spray 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Tea biscuit pans, bake 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: bird of paradise
directions: Dip chicken breasts in eggs, then coat with the cheese.
Fry in the butter or oleo until nice and brown (I use a nonstick pan). Add the wine; cook until chicken is tender.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix and stir all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, butter and rice crispies together.
(Mix will be dry and crumbly.)
Roll into balls.
Dip into melted chocolate and wax.
Chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add banana, milk, oil and egg.
Beat until well blended.

title: eggplant-tomato casserole
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into small pieces.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add green pepper and onion.
Brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and eggplant.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour in baking dish.
Melt remaining butter.
Mix in bread crumbs.
Spread over top.
Add cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Finely chop hot peppers, bell peppers and onions in food processor or by hand.
In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine chopped peppers and onions with remaining items over high heat.
Bring to high boil for 5 minutes, stirring.
Immediately fill pint jars to 1/4 inch of top.
Wipe tops of jar.
Put lids on jars and screw bands on tightly.
Yields 4 pints.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cajun chowder
directions: In a soup pot, combine the roasted garlic butter, oil and onions.
Saute until onions are tender but not browned.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until potatoes are fork tender but not mushy.
Add the mixed vegetables, half & half, black pepper, corn and sausage.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened. This will probably take about 8 to 10 minutes.
If the chowder seems to thicken too much, simply add a little more half and half or water. Taste and add salt, as needed.
I usually add about 1 teaspoon to my pot of chowder but always taste before adding salt and add a little at a time until you get it just right for your palate. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper until ground beef is done.
Drain grease; stir in can of vegetable beef soup and 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring a little while cooking. Then spread on hamburger bun.
Add your favorite mayonnaise, mustard and ketchup.
Eat with chips and enjoy!

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain tuna.
Add soup to milk, and then add mayo.
Add all ingredients to noodles and cook at 350 degrees until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish with crackers.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to pear mixture.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs by hand.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour (test with a toothpick) at 350°. Cool and eat!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except cheese.
Spoon into greased casserole and smooth the top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones; cut in pieces.
Butter a large shallow baking dish well.
Sprinkle part of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix over the bottom of dish.
Place generous layers of chicken next.
tags: cream of mushroom soup and cream of celery soup

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant for 5 minutes in salted water.
Cook sauce (tomato juice, seasonings and onion) until onion is soft.
Drain eggplant and layer with sauce in casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover with cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Add to Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add buttermilk and pecans.
Let cool, then add whipped topping.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or large mold.

title: fudge filling
directions: Place all ingredients together in pan; cook slowly until they boil.
Beat until smooth before spreading.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Mix everything together in a crock-pot.
Cook 1 hour on high. Cook on low, 4 to 8 hours more.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding as package directions using juices as liquid. Drain all fruit well.
Add pudding mixture with fruit. Refrigerate.
Can also use instant pudding if you rather (same measurements).

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour two (9-inch) round baking pans.
In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients. Set aside.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Whip white of egg and add all other ingredients except pecans. Mix thoroughly and add pecans.
Place in a greased pan and toast in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop enough popcorn to make 7-quarts popped corn.
Put popped corn in large roaster pan.
Set aside.

title: tostado dip
directions: Bottom Layer:
1 mashed avocado, 1/2 cup sour cream and 2 tablespoons mayo (mix together).

title: twice baked creamy potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop pulp out.
Mash pulp until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon back into shells.
Bake at 350° until heated, 20 minutes.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Add sausage and bread to egg mixture.
Grease 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Cover in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Put boiling water in Jell-O mixture.
Stir to dissolve. Beat cheese
in until smooth and foamy.	Let chill until syrup consistency.
Add whipped cream.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cut off the tops of broccoli stalks and break into flowerets. Discard large stems.
Boil 2 cups water in saucepan.
Add broccoli and onions.
Cover and cook until very tender.
Do not drain. Place in blender (or chop by hand).
Blend until uniform consistency.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine and cook until clear.
When cool, add 1 cup salad dressing and 3 tablespoons mustard.

title: mama's refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Let cool. Mix yeast and warm water.
Add beaten eggs and flour with the baking powder added to it.
Cover and store in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Mixture will keep in refrigerator 10 days. When ready to bake, shape dough.
Let rise and bake at 375° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: "diet" chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar-free pudding as directed, using skim milk.
Add peanut butter, Sweet 'N Low and vanilla.
Blend together and spoon into pie crust.
May be topped with Cool Whip.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and syrup.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat until fudge is thick.
Add pecans.
Spread on buttered platter.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef and pork together.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and shape into a loaf.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour 1 cup tomato juice over top and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until slightly brown.
Pour off excess juice that is around it and serve warm.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients but beef.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Place beef in a Dutch oven.
Pour sauce on it and stir. Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Do not remove lid until the end of 3 hours.
Remove from oven and shred beef in sauce with 2 forks. Serve on buns.

title: dieter's delight chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken into large chunks.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken and chips(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole. In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion in hot oil 5 minutes or until almost tender.
Add tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce and green chilies.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Stirring occasionally, bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes or until juices are reduced.
Meanwhile, reserve a few tortilla chips.
Lightly crush remaining chips and place in a large bowl.
Pour broth over top; let stand 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In casserole, layer half of the tortilla chips and broth, half of the chicken, half of the cheese and half of the tomato mixture; repeat.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and lightly browned.
Garnish with sour cream, olives and reserved chips.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Place in heavy kettle. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly until thick.
Can as for relish.
Yields 8 half pints.

title: cajun (sweet dough) pie crust
directions: Place margarine and shortening in large bowl and blend with electric mixer until creamy.
Add sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla and blend well by hand.
Add the 10 cups sifted flour, baking powder and salt a little at a time until all has been blended into batter.
Flour table or counter top generously.
Empty dough mixture onto surface.
Knead well.
Measure 4 cups flour into sifter ready for use.
If dough is too soft to roll, add more flour.
It should be easy to handle and should not stick to the fingers.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix together in a large bowl with all the other ingredients.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Use as desired.
This batter will keep several days.
To cook, spoon batter into well-greased muffin tin and bake immediately at 425° for 20 minutes.
You don't wait for rolls to rise before baking.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Spread bottom of pie plate with stuffing.
In skillet, mix tomatoes, butter, drippings, salt and sugar.
Heat until well blended.
Put 1/2 tomato mixture on top of stuffing.
Put 1/2 cheese on top of this.
Place all onions on top of cheese.
Layer remaining tomatoes, then remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Excellent Lenten dish.

title: papaya-cilantro salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 tablespoon of lime juice.
Let stand 1 hour.
Before serving, add the final tablespoon of lime juice.
Serve on poached or grilled fish.

title: bleu cheese bacon potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and dry.
Rub potatoes with extra butter and bake in a 400 degree oven for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from oven.
Cut a lengthwise slice from each potato.
Scoop out inside of each potato.
Mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, bleu cheese, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Spoon mixture lightly into potato shells.
Place on baking sheet and return to hot oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve.

title: west virginia cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add butter to hot milk. Beat eggs. Add sugar. Beat until creamy. Add extracts, dry ingredients, milk
and butter. Beat 2 minutes. Pour into shallow pan and bake 25 minutes in moderately slow oven (350°).

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet until beef is not pink.
Add soup, water, salt, pepper and rice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place cabbage in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam or cooking oil.
Spoon beef mixture over cabbage.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash or whip sweet potatoes and mix with other ingredients. Pour into a greased casserole dish.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts and apples.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and apples with spoon (batter is thick).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in tube or rectangular pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix well and cook fast to begin with.
When it gets thick, cook on low heat. When it forms a hard ball in the water, take it out.
Add soda.
Spread very thin on baking sheet.
Work fast.

title: ginger applesauce bars
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease
and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix gingerbread mix, applesauce, egg and water in medium bowl. Stir
vigorously
with
a fork about 2 minutes or until batter is uniform color and consistency.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spread in	pan.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick
inserted near
center
comes
out
clean.
Spread
with Browned Butter Glaze.
Cut
into
x 1-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: trail cobbler(for dutch oven)
directions: Mix the biscuit mix, sugar, milk and margarine.
Add fruit and stir.
Bake, covered, in oven about 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it doesn't stick to sides of pan.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Combine and bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes, or heat in crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a sauce pan, stirring occasionally after coming to a boil.
Heat one minute.
Then add oats and peanut butter, stirring in good.
Then spoon out on waxed paper.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onion until meat is browned; drain.
Add drained and snipped kraut and 2 tablespoons cracker crumbs.
Combine cream cheese, mustard, garlic salt and pepper. Stir into kraut mixture.
Chill.
Shape into 3/4-inch ball and coat with flour.
Combine eggs and milk; roll kraut balls into egg mixture and then into cracker crumbs.
Heat oil to 375°; deep fry for 30 to 60 seconds, until golden.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef in thin strips; finely chop onion.
Brown meat in margarine and cooking oil; remove from pan.
Saute onion in same pan, then return meat to pan.
Add marjoram, thyme, soup, salt and caraway seed.
Cover; simmer until meat is tender.
Just before serving, add sour cream and sherry.
Heat but do not boil.
Add nutmeg; serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: green bean italiano
directions: In skillet, cook celery, red or green pepper and oregano in oil until tender-crisp. Add beans and heat through. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream
the
margarine and sugar; add eggs and mix well. Add the
crushed
crackers,
pecans,
raisins, soda, salt and flavoring
alternately
with the milk.
Mix very well; bake at 250° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Place peach halves, center up, in pastry shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Sprinkle with nutmeg before baking.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° for until set and crust brown. Serve warm; top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: toasted almond party spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Spread mixture into 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake until golden brown (15 to 20 minutes).
(Ovens vary, may possibly be longer.)
Stir after 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers or cut up pieces of Italian bread.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Combine sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Mash bananas.
Add with flour and vanilla.

title: apricot chicken(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt.
Arrange in 2-quart utility dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over chicken. Cover dish with waxed paper.
Cook 10 minutes in microwave oven. Turn dish 1/2 turn and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop the tomatoes, onions and pepper. Add vinegar, salt and sugar; cook on low heat until mixture becomes a thick sauce, about 45 minutes. Pour into hot jars and seal. Makes about 4 quarts and is good served with peas, beans or meat.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces. Using large casserole dish, layer first 6 ingredients as listed. Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top like frosting. Top with cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: black walnut coconut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well until light and frothy. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating very well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, coconut and flavoring.

title: olive spread for sandwiches or dip
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Put in sealed container and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
It will become thick.

title: eggplant meatballs
directions: Mix all together; form into balls.
Boil or fry.
Drain grease.
Place 1 cup of tomato sauce in the bottom of a baking dish.
Put meatballs on top of sauce.
Can be covered with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.

title: rice
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat 1 1/2 cups milk with Crisco and melt.
Cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Cut up tomatoes, green pepper, onion, olives, cheese and pepperoni; add to macaroni.
Mix together vegetable oil and vinegar; add Good Seasons dressing and Salad Supreme.
Shake/mix well.
Pour over salad and mix.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with your choice of fresh vegetable wedges.

title: lasagna
directions: In a heavy pan, saute onion until clear.
Add beef.
Cook and stir until crumbly.
Stir in seasonings and tomato paste, blended in hot water.
Simmer, uncovered, until blended, about 30 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Spray a skillet with vegetable spray.
Over medium heat, stir rice, onions and garlic in skillet until rice browns slightly. Add tomato sauce, stock, picante sauce, celery, carrots, chili powder, bell pepper and bay leaf.
Stir and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 40 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 6 with 3/4 cup servings, 72 calories, 0.6 grams fat and 2 grams protein.

title: curambethis(greek cookies)
directions: Cream butter well.
Add eggs, sugar, baking powder and whiskey.
Mix well.
Add almonds.
Add enough flour to thicken and roll (about 3 cups).
Roll into size and shape of small finger. Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Dip cold cookies into powdered sugar until well coated.
Makes about 30 dozen.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
While it is heating, prepare the barbecue basting sauce:
Combine the onions, ketchup or peach preserves, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and Tabasco sauce in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart enameled or stainless-steel saucepan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Mix sugars and cinnamon together in a gallon Ziploc bag. Shake biscuit pieces in sugar mixture. Layer coated biscuits and chopped nuts in a Bundt pan. Melt butter and mix with remaining sugar mixture. Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in large skillet.
Combine barbecue sauce and 7-Up, blending well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bring to boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer for about 30 minutes, or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork.

title: sorbetto al limone(lemon sorbet)
directions: Boil the water with the sugar for 5 minutes.
Stir in the lemon juice and let cool, then place in the freezer until hard.

title: mock fillet mignon
directions: Combine meat, oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Shape into 4 patties.
Wrap each
with bacon.
Fasten with toothpicks. Cook on grill 10 to 15 minutes on each side or to desired doneness.
Serve with sauce by sauteing mushrooms in melted butter and adding seasonings.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add confectioners sugar; stir.
Flour cutting board; roll out mixture.
Spread peanut butter on top and roll up.
Slice into thin pieces and serve.

title: instant delight
directions: Mix together butter, flour and nuts and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1 cup of dairy Cool Whip.
Spread over pan mixture. Whip together the pudding mix and milk.
Spread over pan mixture. Spread rest of dairy Cool Whip on top and sprinkle nuts over top.

title: artichoke toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the rye bread.
Spread on thin sliced rye.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma swinehart's peanut butter cookies(1932)
directions: Combine ingredients in given order.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip fork into milk and press balls down to desired size.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken stuffed with rice
directions: Rub chicken with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Brown onions and garlic in skillet in 1/4 cup butter.
Add rice, remaining salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken stock.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry pinwheel cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Stir in vanilla and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal; add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly, 4 or 5 minutes.
Roll dough to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread blueberries over dough; roll up, jelly roll fashion, beginning with long side.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut dough into 12 (1-inch) slices.
Place slices, cut side down, in butter.
Pour sugar syrup around slices; bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: granny gay's bread pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Cook at 375° until brown.
Leave in pan to cool.

title: fish province style
directions: Dip fish in salt, pepper and flour.
Heat oil in skillet. Saute fish until it flakes easily.
Transfer to dish and keep warm.
Add tomatoes to skillet.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add wine, olives and parsley.
Pour sauce over fish and place an anchovy on each slice.
Serves 4.

title: uncooked chili sauce
directions: Add tomatoes and pack in hot jars and seal.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, yet firm.
Slice and put in large mixing bowl.
While still hot, sprinkle with vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients except eggs and parsley.
Gently toss to combine.
Add eggs and parsley, toss again.
Correct seasonings, add more salt, pepper and mayonnaise if desired.
Chill overnight.

title: white bread(2 loaves)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then mix in flour well.
Pour out on floured board.
Knead and roll until you push in on dough and it pops back out.
Place back in bowl.
Oil top.
Cover and let set until double in size.
Then form into two loaves.
Place in Pam sprayed loaf pans.
Oil tops.
Let rise again.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: poor man's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a small greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° until golden.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix both cans of corn with milk, eggs, sugar and crackers. Add 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: quick praline rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift the previously sifted flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
Cut 1/3 c. butter into the mixture until the particles are fine.
Stir in milk, egg, and yeast.
Beat well. (Dough may now be covered with Saran Wrap and stored in refrigerator several hours OR overnight.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into marble size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These freeze well.
Makes 110 marble size balls.

title: mighty good cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix meal, eggs, oil and corn.
Fold in sour cream and mix well.
Pour into a greased skillet and bake until golden brown.
(Cook for about 30 minutes.) Serves eight.

title: brownie cake
directions: Mix in large bowl sugar and flour.
Heat together oleo, water and shortening.
Bring to boil.
Pour over dry mixture and mix. Add cocoa, buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well; spread on greased (large) sheet cake pan (mine's 12 x 17-inches).
Bake at 400 for 20 minutes.
Frost immediately.

title: inexpensive sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until very light. Beat in sugar, salt and flavoring. Mix in butter and hot milk. Sift flour and baking powder together. Beat into mixture. Pour in greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Mix soup with h alf and half and pimiento.
Serves 10.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Put flour in large bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Knead and roll out to about 1/4-inch and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter and fold.
Let rise 45 minutes and bake at 450° until brown.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, peanut butter, egg, vanilla and milk until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls, then press on greased cookie sheet with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove and apply kisses.
Let stand until hard.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Stir together juice of lemon, beaten egg yolk and salt.
Cook until thick.
Cool and stir into whipped cream.
Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit well and dry on paper towels.
Lay in flat casserole, one layer deep.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over fruit.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: cabbage lasagna(4 servings)
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain.
Combine all ingredients except the tomato sauce.
Place in baking dish (6 x 11-inches). Pour sauce over top.
Top with 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: old fashion fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275 degrees. Sift together in 4-quart bowl the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add pecans, candied pineapple,
candied cherries and golden raisins. Mix until fruit and nuts are well coated, set aside.

title: cinnamon cider
directions: In a large saucepan or crock-pot, combine cider, cinnamon, cloves and orange zest.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve mixture into cups.
Add 1 ounce rum to each mug if wanted.
Serve with cinnamon stick.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Crust:
Combine crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press rounded measuring tablespoonfuls of crumb mixture into bottom of each of 6 paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put margarine, water and cocoa in a 3-quart saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool to touch.
When cool, add sugar, soda, flour, salt, eggs and sour cream.
Beat with a wire whisk until smooth.
Place in a large greased pan.
Grease both bottom and sides.
Bake at 350° for 28 minutes.
Best frosting for cake is 1 tub of Betty Crocker milk chocolate frosting.

title: chili con queso
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips, crackers or bread to dip into mixture.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal, let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugar and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs, mix well, sift together flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 package of chocolate chips.
Put batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and remaining chocolate chips on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: ham-how to bake
directions: Soak ham in clear water 24 hours.
Brush until all cure is gone. Leave rind on ham.
Place
in
roaster with rind side up. Bake at 325° for 18 minutes per pound.
When almost done, remove rind and glaze with mixture of ingredients.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and dash of pepper. In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange and alternate layer of potatoes, onion soup mixture and cheese. Dot top with butter. Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 hour. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more or until done.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Sift 6 c. flour with salt and spices. Add molasses and vinegar. Then sifted ingredients. Lastly, add soda dissolved in boiling water. Add more flour if necessary to make soft dough. Bake at 350 degrees 8-10 min.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Cook zucchini in water (3/4 cup) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Melt butter; add onion.
Cook until onion is tender. Add zucchini.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over zucchini. Combine bread crumbs, cheese and some red pepper for garnish. Sprinkle over zucchini and bake until set, 15 to 18 minutes.

title: beef and pasta primavera
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Cook in boiling salted water until crisp-tender.
Drain and put aside. Saute garlic and tomatoes in oil in large skillet or chicken fryer 2 minutes.
Stir in basil and mushrooms.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in peas, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Add to vegetables.
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add mushroom soup, milk and 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Add to 1 pound cooked linguini and toss.
Stir in vegetables and beef.
Heat. Serves 8.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In a saucepan, bring cranberries, sugar and orange juice to a boil, stirring until berries
start to pop.
Then remove from heat and stir in gelatin, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Combine all and pour over flank steak and marinate 4 or more hours, turning occasionally.
Cook on the grill over hot coals about 5 minutes on each side for medium-rare.
Baste with marinade.
Carve in thin slices, cutting on the diagonal.

title: jumbo cheese shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on box; drain.
In a baking dish cover bottom with spaghetti sauce (1 1/2 cups).
Spoon cheese mixture into each shell and put in pan.
Cover top with remaining sauce and a little bit of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese capers
directions: Cut each muffin half into quarters (8 pieces per muffin).
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on toasted muffin.
Broil until bubbly.
Place on paper towel to absorb drippings before serving.

title: no bake peanut butter pie
directions: Blend and beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, creamy peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: grandma's chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
In a large kettle, combine all ingredients except macaroni.
Bring to a boil, then turn down heat and simmer until beans and celery are tender.
Add macaroni and continue to simmer until macaroni is done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease	and
flour
Bundt
cake
pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans in	bottom.
Put cake mix and pudding mix in bowl.	Add rum, water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time; use mixer.
Beat until all
is thoroughly	mixed.	Pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbling and brown.

title: wassail
directions: Mix thoroughly; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Will keep in the refrigerator 4 weeks.

title: austin's fruit salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions. Add all fruit. Fold in 1/2 cup whipped cream. Serves 10.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in
strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil
in
large frying pan.
Add beef and toss over high heat
until
browned.
If not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40
minutes
over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss
until
vegetables are tender and crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix
cornstarch
with
water;
add
to pan. Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through. Preparation time:
20 minutes, Cooking time:
30 to 40 minutes Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, butter, vanilla, sugar, syrup and pecans together. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350 degrees for 30 min.
Center of pie may look soft when shaken but will get firm when cool.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks, hot water, oil, cinnamon and nutmeg; beat well.
Fold in nuts and pineapple with juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: nanna's italian bread
directions: Soften the yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water.
In a large mixing bowl (at least 4 quarts), blend sugar, olive oil, salt and warm water. Add the cool water. Stir in the yeast.
Gradually add the flour until a stiff dough has formed.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and satiny, about 7 to 8 minutes.
Place in a well oiled bowl, turning the dough to oil all sides.
Cover with a damp towel.
Let the dough rise in a warm spot away from drafts until it has doubled in bulk, about 2 hours.

title: sauerkraut cake surprise
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cocoa powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and water, beating after each addition.
Stir in sauerkraut and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Take juices from fruit; add water to make 2 cups.
Heat to boiling point; pour over jello.
Add Coke.
Chill for a while. Add pineapple, cherries and nuts until congealed; then serve. Refrigerate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomatoes and dressing. Pour dressing over.
Just before serving, add tomatoes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stick holes in entire cake.
Bring to boil sugar and milk; boil 1 minute.
Pour over cake.
When cake is cooled, ice with 8 ounces Cool Whip and top with 7 ounces Angel Flake coconut; refrigerate.

title: cherry dream pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla until smooth. Add lemon juice and continue to mix until thick and smooth. Pour into crust and refrigerate 1 hour before serving. Serve with cherry pie filling on top or with fresh strawberries or other fruit toppings.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise and beat until blended. Add dill weed, carrots, cucumber, and green onions and mix well. Makes enough spread for 10 regular sandwiches which I cut into 4 portions, making 40 cocktail sandwiches or will make 20 to 22 open face sandwiches using 3 inch rounds cut from bread slices.
This is also great spread on miniature bagels.

title: punch
directions: Combine all
ingredients and add 1 quart ginger ale and ice immediately before serving.

title: apricot-nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix and gelatin in large mixing bowl.
Add juice and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in a tube pan for one hour at 350°.
Let cool for a few minutes, then turn out on a plate. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crunchy spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into hollowed out, unsliced sourdough bread.
Serve with pieces of bread, assorted raw veggies and crackers.

title: flat apple pie
directions: Mix flour and salt, cut in shortening.
Separate egg.
Put yolk in measuring cup; add milk until 2/3 cup full.
Beat slightly until milk and egg yolk are well mixed. Make a well in middle of flour, pour in milk and egg mixture and mix slightly.
Divide dough into two parts.
Roll out one part and put in jelly roll pan, 15 x 9 x 1.
Cover the dough with 3 handfuls of Wheaties or corn flakes, then thinly sliced apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon to taste and dot with butter.
Cover with remaining dough.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° to 400°.
While hot, spread with icing of 3/4 cup powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.

title: sour cream stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until they are soft in the middle.
Remove them from the oven and cool 5 minutes.
Cut them into halves and scoop out the centers.
In a mixer, blend all of the above ingredients while slowly adding hot potatoes.
With a large spoon, fill the potato shells.
Bake the stuffed potatoes for 20 minutes in a hot oven (400°).
Serve piping hot.

title: mulled cider
directions: In a large saucepan, mix all ingredients, except cinnamon stick garnish, and bring just to a boil.
Cool and strain.
When ready to serve, reheat and pour into cups.
Garnish with cinnamon sticks, if desired.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Combine rest of ingredients in dish and roll chicken breasts in it.
Spray 15 x 10-inch pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, sliced very thin.
Combine onions, pepper and salt.
Mix with 1-quart crushed ice and let stand 1 hour, then wash salt off.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bing to a boil, pack in jars.

title: boiled apple dumpling
directions: Cook apples in sugar, water and butter until soft.
Make dough of flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Mix well.
Drop into cooked apples by small spoon and cook 20 minutes.

title: orange dessert
directions: Stir jello (dry) into Cool Whip until the jello isn't dry. Drain fruit, then add to Cool Whip; add cottage cheese.
Put in large serving bowl and cool several hours before serving.

title: wonder fudge
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, put margarine, chocolate chips, corn syrup and vanilla extract.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in powdered sugar until blended.
Add cereal and stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture evenly in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm and cut into squares to serve.

title: "the original" hershey's fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine cocoa, sugar and salt in heavy 4-quart saucepan. Stir in milk. Bring to bubbly boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil without stirring until mixture reaches 234° (soft-ball stage). Bulb of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of pan. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Do not stir. Cool to 110°; beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss. Quickly spread into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan. Cool and cut into squares. Yield: About 3 dozen candies.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together and drain, add worcestershire, ketchup, and tomato soup.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour spaghetti (cooked and drained) in a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Pour tomato soup mixture over noodles.
Spread cream of celery soup over tomato mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Cook until tender.
Mix together with other ingredients and put in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cook until brown; set aside.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk; beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle with 1/4 caramel topping over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/4 coconut mixture.
Repeat layers.
Serve frozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a hard boil, stirring constantly. Continue until it reaches a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat by hand until smooth. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and cool at room temperature.

title: oven baked fries
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl; spread out onto a cookie sheet. Sprinkle potatoes with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. One-half cup equals 1 starch.

title: company chicken
directions: Pour beaten eggs over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain, then dredge in bread crumbs.
Place 8 tablespoons butter in pan and brown chicken pieces.
Place chicken in baking dish.
In same pan, add remaining 2 tablespoons butter and cook mushrooms 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese. Add broth.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in 8 x 12-inch serving dish. Chill for several hours.
Serve with corn chips and salsa cruda.

title: chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add peanuts, noodles, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of batter on slightly greased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 92 cookies.

title: old-fashioned tomato soup
directions: Heat milk and tomatoes in separate dishes.
When tomatoes boil, add soda and stir until it stops fizzing.
When milk is hot, pour tomatoes into milk, slowly.
Stir.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet and sour steamed cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in narrow wedges and steam in small amount of water until tender. Stir in butter. Combine sugar and vinegar. Pour over cabbage and heat thoroughly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jelly roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch, with aluminum foil or waxed paper; grease.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs about 5 minutes or until very thick and lemon colored.
Pour eggs into large mixer bowl; gradually beat in granulated sugar.
On low speed, blend in water and vanilla. Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt, beating just until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan, spreading batter to corners. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Loosen cake from edges of pan; invert on towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Carefully remove foil; trim off stiff edges if necessary.
While hot, roll cake and towel from narrow end.
Cool on wire rack.
Unroll cake; remove towel.
Beat jelly slightly with fork to soften; spread over cake.
Roll up; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheesy beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat and drain well. Stir in half the salsa and 1 cup of the cheese. Spread 1 cup of the salsa in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Place 1/4 cup meat mixture in the center of each tortilla, then roll up. Place seam side down in the pan on top of the salsa. Top with remaining salsa and the rest of the meat mixture if any is left. Then put the remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and the dish is hot.

title: kolacky
directions: Warm oven to 350°.
Cream the cream cheese and butter until round ball.
Gradually add 2 cups flour.
Cream until mixed well. Roll out dough until very thin.
(Roll out dough a little at a time.)
Cut into 1 x 1-inch square.
Put on cookie sheet.
Put pie filling or any other filling in the middle.
Bring all four corners of the dough to the middle.
Bake 10 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Color with red food coloring; cool.
Add strawberries.
Fill crust.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrots and onions in butter until squash looks clear.
Mix bread crumbs, sour cream and chicken soup in large bowl.
Add squash mixture to bread crumb mixture; mix together. Place in casserole pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with shredded cheese and heat just until cheese melts.

title: coconut bars
directions: Cream oleo and 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 cup flour and mix well.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Mix remaining 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour.
Blend in eggs, vanilla and salt.
Fold in pecans and coconut.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a saucepan, mix together sugar, syrup and water.
Cook on high heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking until it begins to string off spoon.
Add peanuts, stirring until peanuts start to "smell done" and pop open.
Add butter.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and mix well.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix sugar, Kool-Aid and 2 quarts water.
Add jello mixture and pineapple juice.
Better if allowed to stay in freezer until ready to serve.
Take out 1 hour before serving.
Add 7-Up before serving.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Saute margarine and onion.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and spices.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in tomato juice.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir hot tomato mixture into cold milk.
Heat almost to boiling and serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Mix cornbread mix as package directs with eggs and milk.
Add cottage cheese, thawed broccoli and onion.
Pour into butter filled dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs with milk. Add 1 tablespoon melted Crisco and the corn.
Drop from teaspoon into hot Crisco.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: creamy tomato dill soup
directions: Over low heat in a 3 quart saucepan saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 3 minutes. Remove from heat, add tomato paste.
In a small bowl stir flour and half a cup of water until smooth.
Add to soup.
Gradually stir in remaining water and bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook 2 minutes.
Place the soup in a mixer, process until smooth. Return puree to pan.
Add whip cream and dill.

title: east indian dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream in saucepot; bring to a boil.
Simmer; stirring until mixture is blended. Remove from heat; cool.
Blend in sour cream.
Mixture thickens slightly on standing.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cocoa, peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Spoon by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: quick-n-cool summer salad
directions: Prepare and cook macaroni.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 8 people.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water; add to potato mixture.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Dissolve flour in 1/4 cup of milk; stir into soup.
Add remaining milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 25 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine eggs and oil and beat until light and fluffy. Continue beating while you add sugar, vanilla, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: connie's chocolate chess pie
directions: Heat the butter, chocolate and sugar together over low heat on top of stove until butter and chocolate are melted.
Blend all together.
Remove from heat and add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until filling is set.

title: raspberry-applesauce jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Put in fridge until slightly thickened.
Add raspberries (including liquid) and applesauce.
Mix and pour into mold.
Chill until set.

title: lentils and rice soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight (after rinsing and cleaning).
Add to 4 quarts cold water.
Add lamb, celery, garlic, crushed tomatoes, salt, pepper and herbs.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 1 hour. Remove lamb from pot and cut off bones.
Return to pot.
Add carrots and rice.
Simmer another 15 to 20 minutes or when rice is tender.
Serve with hot Italian or French bread.
Makes enough to freeze for another meal! A great winter warmer-upper.

title: golden western cake
directions: *One pound Imperial brown sugar may be substituted for powdered sugar.

title: macaroni-sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
Place in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and mix with meat.
Combine soup and milk; heat.
Stir in eggs and cheese.
Pour over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.
(Ready-fixed casserole may be frozen.
Thaw before baking.)

title: curried chicken salad stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, mustard and garlic.
Add chicken, red peppers, celery, sunflower seeds and scallions.
Toss lightly.
Spoon about 1 1/2 tablespoons filling into each shell. Chill.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ice cream churn.
(Half and half may be substituted for some of the milk for a creamier ice cream.)
Add enough milk to fill to 1 gallon line.
Churn and enjoy!

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Chop onion and cook in a little water.
Add other ingredients; stir.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare hamburg according to taco mix.
Layer on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream and garlic powder/salt (sprinkled) together and spread over beef.
Chop tomato, pepper, scallions and olives; mix together.
Spread vegetables over next layer.
Pour salsa on top.
Spread shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: asparagus carrot casserole
directions: Cook raw carrots 15 to 20 minutes.
Layer 1/2 carrots, 1/2 asparagus, 1/2 almonds and margarine, making 2 layers.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour over layered ingredients.
Top with cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (If asparagus is fresh, cut in 1-inch lengths.)

title: giant peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, followed by peanut butter chips.
Thin with liquid and/or shortening.
Object is to cause cookies to flatten as cooking.
You will learn how much as you make them.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream eggs and shortening.
Add pumpkin, oil and vanilla and mix well.
Combine flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nutmeg; beating well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: syrup bread
directions: Cream butter and syrup; add eggs and blend well.
Combine sifted flour and soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Cook in a black iron skillet at 350° until done.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix vinegar and dry mustard.
Let set overnight.

title: creole pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain; add green pepper and onions.
Cook until almost done.
Stir in 1/4 cup flour, salt, pepper and tomatoes and cook until smooth, blended and thick.
Can also add cooked vegetables such as corn, green beans, peas, etc.
Can serve on top of cornbread or biscuits if desired.

title: my traditional christmas fruitcake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add water, syrup and grape juice with 1 teaspoon of rum extract, then add 1/2 the flour.
Mix the other half of the flour with the candied fruit and pecans. Add spices, raisins and currants to egg mixture.
Mix in candied fruit mixture.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for 4 hours over a pan of water.
Makes 11 or 12 (1 pound) fruitcakes.

title: amaretto
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add almond extract and bitters.
Let cool and add vodka.
Mix well.
Put in gallon jar with lid.
Cover and let sit 30 days.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain berries and pineapple; use 1 cup of the juice in Jell-O mixture.
Stir in fruit.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan; cool in refrigerator until firm.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel six apples; slice and place in bottom of baking dish. Mix together cake mix, sugar and cinnamon and pour over apples. Melt butter and drizzle over top of dry batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden frosting
directions: Lightly brown butter. Remove from heat. Add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Add water until spreading consistency.
Use on Stuffed Date Cookies.

title: graham cracker pecan cookies
directions: Melt butter and sugar together and boil until caramelized. Toss in nuts.
Spread graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Top with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and place on racks.

title: red chicken and vegetable soup(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine tomatoes (undrained), vegetable juice, undrained corn, onion, squash and celery.
Cook covered on High for 8 to 10 minutes (until boiling). Stir and cook 8 to 12 minutes longer until vegetables are tender (stirring once).
Stir in undrained chicken.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Layer Twinkies in 9 x 13-inch pan, cream side up.
Heat until melted chocolate chips, margarine or butter and water.
Pour over top of Twinkies.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over chocolate. Sprinkle with crushed nuts. Refrigerate.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs, milk, flour and vanilla. Mix well, Turn onto floured board. Roll out and cut into circles with cookie cutter.

title: skewered grilled potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and water in a casserole dish and cover. Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.
(Stir after 8 minutes.) Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in potatoes; cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain and arrange potatoes on skewers.
Place on grill over hot coals.
Grill, covered, about 4 minutes. Rotate; brush with dressing and continue grilling 4 more minutes.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a large jelly-roll pan. While cake is warm, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Then pour butterscotch topping over cake (may want to use new fat-free).
Cool.
Use Cool Whip or like and spread on cake. Crush Heath bars and sprinkle on top.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Stir eggs, soup, tuna and pimentos; set aside.
Mix well the Bisquick mix and hot water.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth.
Press dough in bottom and sides of a greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on dough.
Add tuna mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center sets.
Cool before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, margarine and oil with pastry blender.
Stir in flour with fork.
Roll on and between wax paper.
Makes two crusts.
Bake
filled
pie at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Serve with apple slices dipped in pineapple juice to prevent browning.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage, onion and celery.
Add and mix the rest of the ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 250°, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to directions; drain.
Add 1 can undiluted mushroom soup.
Mix together and put in 8 x 8-inch glass casserole dish.
Cover with the shredded cheese.
Cover with croutons and pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: miss carrie mae's banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
For bread, pour into loaf pans and adjust baking time.
May be frozen.

title: old fashioned syrup tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening.
Add syrup.
Add egg.
Beat until mixed well.
Add flour and vanilla or nutmeg.
Pour on floured sheet and roll out; cut or make small balls and press flat.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cook on greased cookie sheet.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips over low heat.
Stir until completely dissolved. Add peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Then it is ready for the candy dish.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices in mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, butter and chocolate chips in a saucepan. Put cereal in a bowl and pour mixture over it.
Stir until coated. Cool it a little.
Put 2 cups powdered sugar in a plastic trash bag, dump in cereal and shake to coat.
Dump back into bowl. Happy eating!
Arf, Arf.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Heat oven to 250° to 275°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruits, until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruits.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients well together; chill and serve.
Nuts and miniature marshmallows may be added.

title: bagels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup of warm water (105° to 115°).
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir yeast; add oil and stir again.
