Add to the center of the flour mixture, stirring gently.
Add slightly beaten egg.
Stir briskly to form a ball of dough and knead on a floured board for 2 minutes.
Return dough to mixing bowl, smooth side up, and punch down 3 times.
Cover and let rise at room temperature for 30 minutes or until dough has come to the top of the bowl.
Knead again on board until smooth and elastic as for rolls.
Divide dough into 12 equal portions.
Form into rings, 3/4-inch thick.
Place on a floured cookie sheet and slip under broiler for 3 minutes. Remove from oven.
Drop each bagel into rapidly boiling water a few at a time so they do not touch each other, and cook for 15 to 20 seconds.
Remove and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then increase heat to 400° for 10 minutes or until bagels are brown and crust is crisp.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: gingersnap cake
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place one gingersnap in each muffin cup.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour over gingersnaps, filling 3/4 full.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool and top with fruit, chocolate chips, nuts, preserves or any topping of your choice, or enjoy plain.

title: play dough(for children)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Work with hands.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: molasses bran bread
directions: Dissolve soda in molasses.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy pickles
directions: Put vinegar, sugar and spices into pan and boil for 5 minutes. Pour over cukes and onions and refrigerate for at least a day. Enjoy.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, milk, cocoa and butter; boil for only 1 minute. Add the peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla; mix together.
Drop on foil.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in pie plate.
Put refried beans on top, then chilies.
Spread cheese over whole dish.
Put olives and scallions over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or can be heated in microwave.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: First Layer:
Mix butter, flour, sugar and salt.
Press in pizza pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 325° and let cool.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Combine green pepper, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring this to a boil.
Add squash and onion; let simmer, then return to a boil.
Pack pickles into hot, sterilized jars.
Cover with vinegar mixture and seal.
Yield: 2 quarts.

title: cuban chicken
directions: Mix all spices together.
Rub in chicken.
Let stand one hour. Fry in hot oil 20 minutes on each side.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar and let stand while making jello and it is cooling.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool until thick.
Add fruit mixture and place in pan. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce with a dab of mayonnaise on top.

title: mother mac's banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
With electric mixer, cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, mashed bananas, vanilla and dry ingredients and blend well. Add chopped pecans.
Pour batter in 9 x 5 x 2-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Mix last 4 ingredients together. In a casserole dish; layer 1/4 of the cracker crumb mix. Then, on top of this, layer 1/2 of the chicken mixture. Finish by alternating layers ending with crumb mix. Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: chess bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix with 1 egg. Press into pan.
Mix together softened cream cheese, eggs (3), vanilla and confectioners sugar. Mix nuts into mixture.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: veal or pork mozzarella(microwave recipe)
directions: Pound cutlets to 1/8-inch thickness.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, cook butter on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until melted.
Dip cutlets in butter, then lightly coat with crumbs.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, cool, peel and slice potatoes.
Fry bacon and crumble. Put over potatoes with 5 tablespoons bacon grease.
Add sliced green onions.
Into pan, put water, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch and a little water.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Set aside for 2 hours to enhance flavor.
You may slice hard-boiled eggs on top, if you wish.

title: quick coconut pie(mix in blender)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bottom of blender.
Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased pie plates and let stand for 5 minutes.
Press coconut into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: taco rice casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add the tomatoes, taco mix and rice.
Place all in casserole; bake for 30 minutes to 1 hour, until rice is cooked.
Add grated cheese on top; heat until melted.
Can be made in crock-pot.

title: tropical nut bread
directions: Blend well the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with bananas to margarine mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Add rice and brown.
Add mushrooms and stir a few minutes.
Add soups and bring to a boil. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling water. Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts (reserve some nuts). Mix and pour into long Pyrex dish. Refrigerate to gel. Spread sour cream on top and sprinkle nuts on top of sour cream.

title: roast beef
directions: Dust beef and brown in oil.
Take meat out
and
put
in onions and garlic and brown lightly.
Replace meat	and add all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: marinated pasta
directions: Mix together everything. Refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix flour, salt, dry mustard, pepper and milk.
Microwave on High until it begins to thicken.
Add margarine and 2 cups cheese. Cook macaroni until done.

title: muffin pizza melt
directions: Preheat broiler.
Spread 1 tablespoon sauce over each muffin half.
Season evenly with oregano, crumbling leaves as you sprinkle.
Top each muffin with a sprinkling of 1 tablespoon Mozzarella and 1/2 teaspoon Parmesan cheese.
Set pizza muffins 4 to 6 inches from heat and broil until cheese is melted and bubbling, 2 to 3 minutes.
These are quick, easy, tasty and low in calories.

title: french chicken soup
directions: Bring the broth to a boil over medium heat.
Cool slightly. Ladle the soup into mugs.
Top each serving with a spoonful of sour cream and a few walnuts.
Serve immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of an 8-inch square or 1 1/2-quart baking dish with golden vanilla wafers.
Combine pudding mix, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Layer slices of banana over vanilla wafers, then add a layer of pudding.
Repeat layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream or topping and garnish with banana slices.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in vegetable oil until transparent. Add uncooked rice.
Brown rice slightly, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, salt, bouillon and water.
Cook until rice is done.

title: swiss potatoes
directions: Prepare the potatoes according to instructions.
Beat the egg into the potatoes.
Cut the cheese into strips and mix into the potatoes.
Place a few of the strips on top of the casserole. Bake in the oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown. Sprinkle with a little paprika.
Yields 4 servings.

title: gingerbread pancakes
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add buttermilk, water and coffee.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Combine the two mixtures and add melted margarine.
Cook on griddle as any other pancakes.
Serve with honey, maple syrup or molasses.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups of batter or 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together the cheese, onion, milk, horseradish and crab. Sprinkle butter and almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes, or zap in microwave.
May be frozen.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix hamburger, onion soup mix, egg, milk and bread (pinched into small pieces) together.
Roll into desired size balls in palms of hands.

Heat oil in frying pan. Put meatballs, one layer at a time and cook until brown on all sides. Remove. Drain oil from pan. Put mushroom soup plus one can of water in pan. Return to heat. Mix until smooth.
Put meatballs into pan. Simmer 20 minutes with lid on. Add more water if necessary. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: russian cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake in well oiled skillet for 30 minutes at 425°.

title: aunt bea's double quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, beaten egg, shortening and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour; stir until smooth.
Scrape batter from side of bowl.
Cover, let rise in warm place (or over hot water) until double, about 30 minutes.
Stir down batter.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups, filling each about 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Cover. Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 15 minutes.

title: broccoli stuffed tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes thoroughly.
Cut off tops and scoop out pulp, leaving shell intact.
Reserve pulp for other uses.
Sprinkle cavities of tomatoes with salt and pepper and invert on wire rack to drain for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; stuff with cream cheese.
Top with piece of bacon.
Broil until bacon browns.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, salad oil, sugar, vanilla and pumpkin. Add sifted dry ingredients. Mix well. Bake in an 11 x 17 inch pan at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa.
Stir until well blended.
Add other ingredients.
Stir together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill 1 hour. Serve with bread chunks or fresh vegetables.

title: layered shrimp appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Spread over bottom of 10-inch round dish.
Spread cocktail sauce evenly over cream cheese mixture.
Top with shrimp, cucumber and onion. Refrigerate until serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
(110 calories per serving.)

title: black magic cake
directions: Can be mixed by hand or mixer until well blended.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 35 minutes. Good with buttercream icing.

title: zucchini bites
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease bottom and sides of rectangular pan, 13x9x2 inches.
Stir all ingredients until blended.
Spread in pan. Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into 2 inch squares; cut squares diagonally in half into triangles.

title: caramel brownies
directions: By hand, mix together cake mix, 1/3 cup of the Pet milk, walnuts and melted butter.
Flatten 1/2 of this mixture in 13 x 9-inch aluminum pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Beat eggs, salt and pepper.
Add salmon and mix.
Put in frying pan as you would fry pancakes.
Brown on both sides. Serves 6.

title: gee jo's chocolate fudge cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine, set aside.
Combine flour and sugar (mix with spoon).
Add 1 egg at a time, stir as little as possible.
Add margarine and chocolate mixture, vanilla and nuts. Spoon into cupcake papers.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Mix well and bake 1 hour at 350° in a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: quick corn fritters
directions: Blend egg and milk.
Add pancake mix.
Fold in corn.
Drop by teaspoon in 1-inch of hot fat.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: tex-mex souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat inside of 2 1/2-quart souffle dish with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Separate eggs, placing yolks in small bowl and whites in large bowl.
Let whites come to room temperature.
Place milk, flour and chili powder in 2 cup jar with tight fitting lid; shake until smooth.
Pour into medium size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat; mix in cheese until melted.
Stir in chilies, ham and egg yolks.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Using clean beaters, beat egg whites at high speed until stiff, but not dry peaks form.
Gently but thoroughly fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
With rubber spatula, cut down through the center of the whites, across the bottom of the bowl and up the side, turning the bowl as you fold.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until puffy, browned on top and souffle shakes slightly when rack is gently moved back and forth.
Serve immediately.

title: creamy chicken broccoli noodles
directions: In saucepan, cook noodles according to package directions. Add seasoning packet; drain off most of liquid.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat through, stirring often.

title: mcqueen cheese ball
directions: Mix all but nuts in a bowl. Put in refrigerator until set, then remove and shape into ball. Roll in nuts.

title: "the" champagne punch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour over ice ring. Serves 50.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into large greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve on your favorite bun.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereals into large bowl; set aside.
In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.

title: clipper chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Using electric mixer, beat first 6 ingredients in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Stir into butter mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and all chopped nuts. Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until cookies are golden brown, about 16 minutes.
Transfer cookies to racks to cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in the blender except for the oil, poppy seeds and red food coloring.
Pour in a little oil and start to blend.
Pour the oil in a tiny stream until is all emulsified. Add poppy seeds and food coloring as dark as you would like.
Food coloring is optional, but looks prettier on fruit.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Arrange apples in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork; sprinkle over apples.
Bake until apples are tender and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve with cream, ice cream or hard sauce, if desired.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg and salt.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet and brown meatballs. Remove meatballs to bowl.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Heat skillet and drippings to medium heat.
Stir in flour and 1 teaspoon salt; cook for 1 minute.
Stir in milk and water, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add meatballs.
Heat to medium and cook.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes. Serve with potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together and add the dressing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients, then add peanut butter. Mix in remaining ingredients. Chill dough. Form into balls, dip into sugar and place on cookie sheet. Use fork to flatten. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown. Approx. 8-10 minutes.

title: butternut squash
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, and vanilla.
Mash squash and add to the mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated carrots and green beans
directions: Rinse beans, snip off ends.
Pare carrots and cut into thin strips (about 3 inches long).
Combine beans and carrots in saucepan, cover with lightly salted water.
Cover with lid and cook until just tender (about 10 minutes).

title: zucchini bread
directions: (Just add more flour to make real good cookies also.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cut up cheese into cubes and melt in saucepan (over low heat). In
a
separate pan brown hamburger.
Add hamburger to melted cheese with remaining ingredients.	Serve hot with corn or nacho chips.
(To keep warm, serve in small crock-pot.)

title: chasity's rice surprise
directions: Melt bark in microwave.
Add peanut butter, Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Spoon on wax paper and chill.

title: "stuff"
directions: Mix ingredients together, except almond bark.
Melt almond bark in microwave and pour over mix.
Spread on wax paper.
Break up and eat.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Blend milk and flour well; add to vegetables.
Cook until blended and soup thickens.
Add the cubed cheese and stir until melted.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop corn.
Mix remainder of ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Good!
Good!

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add vanilla, flour and potato chips. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
After baking, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: italian butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, egg yolks and sugar.
Add ingredients to butter mixtures.
Mix like pie dough between wax paper.
Cut in strips 1 x 4-inches.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: popovers for two
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Generously grease 4 (6 ounce) custard cups. Beat all ingredients in a small bowl with beater.
Pour batter evenly into prepared custard cups.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Serve hot with butter and jams.

title: good old blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugars, shortening and vanilla. Combine salt, cinnamon, flour and baking powder.
Add to creamy mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish and top with sweetened fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour.

title: pie crust for one
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening.
Mix water and flour.
To blend your dough, cut with pastry knife, or use a few butter knives.
Add mixture of flour and water; mix together.
Form a ball and roll out for pie pans.

title: egg head cones
directions: Take desired amount of wafer ice cream cones and put on a workable surface; fill with scrambled eggs.
Top with bacon bits.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix in sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and pull each section apart into very small pieces.
Chop onion.
Add all other ingredients and chill over 8 hours. Serve.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt in the top of a double boiler the butterscotch bits.
Add the can of peanuts and mix well.
Add the chow mein noodles and mix well.
Drop small amounts (about a tablespoonful) onto wax paper to cool.
Serves as desired.

title: roast beef with bearnaise cream
directions: In processor, blend cream cheese with butter.
Add reduced mixture, lemon juice, pepper and a few drops Tabasco.
Blend, then taste to correct seasonings and consistency.
Chill.
Spread on slices of medium rare roast beef, roll, then chill until firm. Cut into 1-inch pieces before serving.

title: apricot frost
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1 cup syrup.
Mix gelatin, sugar, syrup, and egg yolks.
Heat, stirring until mixture comes to boil. Remove from heat.
Sieve apricots.
Add to gelatin.
Add lemon juice.
Stir in milk and cream.
Freeze firm in refrigerator trays. Break in chunks and beat smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Freeze firm in trays.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: herb-seasoned chicken nuggets(low-fat)
directions: Trim all visible fat from chicken; cut in 1-inch cubes.
In a medium bowl, mix egg and water.
Add chicken; stir to coat well. In a small bowl, mix next 7 ingredients.
With a fork, mix well to distribute it evenly.
Transfer the crumbs to a plastic or paper bag, working in batches, add the chicken to the bag and shake well to coat each piece.
Coat a jelly roll pan with Pam.
Add the chicken pieces in a single layer; leave a little space between them.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn the pieces over and bake 5 minutes more or until lightly browned and crisp.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat until cheese melts. Add more milk if mixture is too thick.
Serve with tortilla chips (unsalted).

title: mandle bread
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and sugar until creamy.
Mix flour with baking powder and add to margarine mixture.
Add nuts and cranberries to mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 5 (5 3/4 x 3 1/4-inch) loaf pans sprayed with Baker's Joy. When cooled, slice and place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Place in oven for 5 to 10 minutes until slightly browned.

title: lazy day cabbage
directions: Brown hamburger, rice and onion soup mix and add tomato soup. Mix and pour over cabbage.
Cut into small strips.
Bake in a 3-quart dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions; add to softened cream cheese.
Add ham.
Mix together by hand and form a ball.
Place on serving plate.
Eat with crackers or chips.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine. Add rest of ingredients. Roll in wax paper. Chill overnight. Cut and bake in a 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Spray griddle and heat pork chops on both sides. When they change color to white, sprinkle spices on each side and continue on griddle until light brown. Remove and place in casserole dish. Prepare rice and vermicelli according to directions but use 1/2 stick of butter and add cream of celery soup. Once rice is tender, add green beans with water and mix. Pour this over top of pork chops. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In medium saucepan combine water, carrots and broccoli.
Cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes or until tender-crisp; drain.
In a bowl combine pasta, carrots and broccoli; toss gently.

title: pat in pan pie crust
directions: In a bowl, put the oil, boiling water and milk.
Add flour and salt; whip with fork until smooth and thick.
Stir until dough forms a ball.
Pat in pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: health muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add liquids in order listed. Mix well and store in refrigerator in tightly covered container. (Keeps a month.)
Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook spinach and drain well.
In large bowl beat eggs; add cheeses, spinach and seasonings and mix well. Add drained sausage meat.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In a saucepan combine flour, sugar, juice, vinegar and egg. Heat until thick; keep stirring.
Cool about 40 minutes.

title: dolie's buttermilk rolls(cir. 1890)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald buttermilk.
Add sugar, salt, fat and soda.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into rolls. Place on greased pan or a cookie sheet.
Top with melted fat and cover.
Let rise in warm place until they double in size.
Bake in a heated oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: roxanne's favorite green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup, milk, salt, pepper and half can of onions. Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add rest of onions last few minutes to brown.

title: coconut mochi
directions: Mix everything except for sesame seed in one bowl and have a floured, greased 9 x 13-inch pan ready.
Place the sesame seed in a small frying pan and toast.
Place mixture in pan and sprinkle generously with sesame seed.
Place in oven and bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Very easy.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter-banana cake
directions: Mix cake batter as you usually do, except add the stick of butter and substitute milk for any water called for.
Add all but 2 tablespoons of the peanut butter to the batter and mix well. Then fold in bananas.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cake is completely cooled, add the remaining peanut butter to your prepared icing and frost.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix together all ingredients except bread, meat and cheese.
Lay bread cubes in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle meat over cubes and cheese over meat.
Pour other ingredients over all.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Let stand out 15 minutes before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered (makes 12 pieces).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and pat dry with damp cloth or paper towel. Chop stems finely.
Beat cheese with milk and Worcestershire sauce until light and fluffy.
Add chopped stems, water chestnuts, green pepper, onion and bacon.
Blend well.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter (left to soften) with sugar. Beat.
Add flour and eggs, then flavoring.
Begin with cold stove at 275° for 1 hour, 300° for 1 hour.
Put 1 pan of water under cake.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat, drain fat and season with salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Add carrots and celery and let simmer.
Place meat mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Over the meat layer first the green beans, then the corn, then onion, then cheese.
Over the cheese cover with prepared mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over potatoes.
Make sure the dish is well covered with the mashed potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute chopped medium onion in margarine.
Add mushroom soup. Mix broccoli, cooked rice, cream of mushroom and sauteed onion in margarine.
Sprinkle in ground red pepper.
Salt to taste.
Mix well in casserole dish.
Cover evenly on top with melted Cheez Whiz.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's pumpkin squares with cool whip topping
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and press in 10 x 14-inch pan, greased and floured or sprayed with Pam.

title: hamburger cornbread
directions: Mix batter for cornbread and pour 1/2 of the batter in the bottom of a large greased cast-iron skillet.
Add meat, onion and pepper in layers, adding cheese last.
Cover with remainder of the cornbread batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: herbed zucchini bake
directions: In medium mixing bowl, toss 3/4 cup of croutons with 2 tablespoons melted butter; set aside.
In large saucepan, cook zucchini in lightly salted water until barely tender (5 minutes). Drain.
Cook carrots and onions in 1/4 cup butter until tender. Add remaining croutons, soup, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in cooked squash.
Spread in ungreased 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Top with more croutons. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture, mixing until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick and easy cream of broccoli soup
directions: Empty cans of soup in saucepan.
Add water or milk and mix well. Partially cook broccoli as package directs and add to soup. Simmer on medium heat until soup is smooth and creamy.

title: new cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients gently.
Bake in greased pan at 425° until brown and crusty on top.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Spoon over 8 ounce cream cheese block.
Spread on crackers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Stir the shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat thoroughly. Sift together the dry ingredients; add to molasses mixture alternately with boiling water, beating after each addition until smooth.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in moderate oven, 350°, for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Cut in squares and top with whipped cream.

title: beat - don't knead rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
With spoon, beat in remaining flour.
Chill 2 hours before making out rolls.
(Can be kept in refrigerator for 1 week.)

title: louisiana beef stew
directions: Combine flour and seasonings and sprinkle on beef cubes. Brown in hot fat.
Add tomatoes, onions, vinegar and molasses. Bring to boil.
Simmer for 2 hours then add carrots and raisins. Cook for 30 more minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes. This dish can be made in a crock-pot.

title: browned rice
directions: Wash rice; let drain.
Fry onions in oil to brown.
Remove and fry rice golden brown.
Add all ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Set power select at Medium-high.
Combine all ingredients and shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs (about 20).
Arrange in oblong baking dish and heat 7 1/2 to 8 1/2 minutes, draining liquid and rearranging meatballs once.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Mix soup with cream cheese (will be thick) and pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers; mix with butter and spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate-rum-almond sauce(microwave)
directions: Place half and half, sugar and chocolate in a 4-cup microwave-safe measure.
Cover loosely with waxed paper and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring twice, until chocolate is melted.
Stir in butter, nuts and extract.
Pour into glass jar and refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.

title: blueberry orange salad
directions: Bring orange juice to boil in saucepan over medium heat. Remove.
Add jello, sugar and lemon rind.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Chill mixture until it is the consistency of an egg white.
Stir in buttermilk; mix well.
Fold in blueberries; pour into an oiled 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate until set.
May be unmolded onto lettuce leaves.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and oil.
Stir in flour to form one lump.
Allow dough to rise for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Press dough onto pizza pan, top with your favorites, and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: jewelry cleaner
directions: Soak for 5 minutes.
Brush lightly; dry.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet with Crisco; sprinkle with flour.
Mix ingredients into cookie batter.
Drop 2 large tablespoons to each cake.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: lemon icebox frozen pie
directions: Make graham cracker crust to fit into 9 x 13-inch pan (don't cook).
Mix egg yolks, 6 tablespoons sugar, lemon rind and 2 tablespoons lemon juice together in large bowl; set aside.
Beat together until stiff the 2 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar. Fold into large bowl mixture; set aside.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice to chilled milk; beat until thick and fold into mixture. Pour into crust and freeze until firm.

title: meat balls
directions: Put ground beef in a large bowl and crack in at least 2 large eggs, depending on amount of meat being used.
Add some finely chopped onion, green pepper and garlic; then add bread crumbs, just enough to hold together when trying to roll into balls.
Too much bread crumbs will make meat balls dry.
Brown meat balls or just roll and drop into spaghetti sauce.

title: cheese roll
directions: Combine all ingredients into long rolls; sprinkle with chili powder.
Serve with crackers.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Break crackers in pieces.
Mix with dry ingredients. Beat egg whites very stiff and fold into dry ingredients.
Bake in greased square pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy chili
directions: Mix ground meat and onion; brown.
Drain fat.
Combine the other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: bavarian cabbage soup(chowder)
directions: In pan, brown sausage.
Add carrots, seed and butter.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Reduce heat; stir often.
Serves 8 cups.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly; form into balls.
Put into baking dish.
Cover with your favorite gravy or sauce and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
This makes good spaghetti and meat balls.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and bake.

title: baked flounder fillets
directions: Place fish in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes. Serves 2.

title: cashew chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to chicken mixture, adding just enough to moisten.
Cover and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and corn tortilla soup
directions: Place all ingredients in steam kettle. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Adjust seasoning to taste. Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch strips. Deep-fry 2 minutes or until light brown. Serve soup in bowl. Sprinkle strips in soup.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli just to thaw. Drain.
Mix all ingredients with broccoli except Parmesan cheese.
Pour ingredients into pie shells. Top with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese each.
Bake 40 to
45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot sausage and cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and green onions until sausage is browned.
Pour off fat.
Stir in Cheddar cheese soup/sauce and water.
Heat until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mu's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar and egg. Dump in flour.
Let rise to double size.
Knead down and make into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add oil and stir.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add gradually to egg, sugar and oil mixture.
Fold in apples, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or a Bundt pan.
Put in a cold oven and cook at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce and flour together well. Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until bubbling.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over it and serve.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Season chops to taste, brown chops in oil and season while browning.
Remove from skillet and add vegetables and rice, stir until rice is golden brown.
Stir in broth and thyme.
Put in casserole and top with chops and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa, vanilla, and milk.
Boil until thick, remove from heat immediately, mix in peanut butter, oatmeal, and nuts.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Cool and enjoy!

title: blueberry ring cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease or flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Cut margarine into 1/3 cup of cake mix (dry) in small bowl until crumbly.
Mix in brown sugar and nuts; reserve.
Beat eggs slightly with fork; stir in sour cream.
Mix in remaining cake mix (batter will be thick and slightly lumpy).
Stir in blueberries.
Spread 1/2 of the batter (about 2 cups) in pan; sprinkle with reserved crumbly mixture.
Spread with remaining batter.
Bake until golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Spread with glaze.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Fry bacon. Drain and crumble.

title: lobster salad
directions: Cut the lobster meat into large bite size pieces; place them in a bowl and add the celery.
Blend the mayonnaise and cream in a small bowl, then gently combine with the lobster.
Toss to mix and add salt.
Arrange a bed of lettuce leaves and put the salad on top.

title: punch
directions: Mix well and add enough water to fill a gallon container. Pour in punch bowl and add a half gallon container of orange or pineapple sherbet.

title: orange cake
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Blend with electric mixer 30 seconds on low speed;
beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, and remove from pans. Mix juice and powdered sugar.
Prick holes in warm cake;
pour juice mixture over cake.

title: stuffed crab or crab cakes
directions: Saute onion, celery, garlic, bell pepper and parsley in butter. Mix crab meat, bread crumbs, eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg; mix well. Combine sauteed vegetables with crab mixture and thoroughly mix. Put in crab shells or form patties. Dip shells or patties into mixture of egg and milk, then in bread crumbs or fish fry. Drop in hot oil and fry until hot throughout or bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: veal or chicken marsala
directions: Lightly flour tenders; cut into small pieces.
In large skillet with oil, brown meat.
Add onion, garlic and oregano; cook until onion is almost done.
Add salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon flour; add wine and broth.
Cook until it thickens.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let marinate overnight.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and oil with dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Spoon on hot waffle iron after spraying iron with Pam.

title: basic uncooked buttercream frosting
directions: Put butter into a small mixer bowl.
Cream for a few seconds. Stop mixer.
Add sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Beat until blended and fluffy.
Add a little more sugar, if necessary, for spreading consistency.

title: pasta gardena
directions: Cook pasta according to package; drain well.
Combine oil and vinegar in jar; cover and shake vigorously.
In large skillet, combine cooked pasta, oil-vinegar mixture and tomatoes.
Heat over low heat, tossing gently.
Add parsley, basil, salt and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Pour into a gallon jar; do not screw lid on tight and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Perfect for No. 7 iron skillet.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Grate onion, celery and carrot. While boiling, add parsley, salt and pepper. When potatoes are cooked, add milk, soup and margarine.
Simmer to blend flavors.

title: cranberry orange loaf
directions: Combine in medium bowl flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Then mix well in small bowl, shortening, orange juice, egg, orange zest, and almond extract. Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Fold in cranberries and pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan 10 minutes and then remove and cool completely on wire rack.

title: cherry party punch
directions: Dissolve soft drink powder in water and sugar.
Stir in juices and chill.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Alternate flour and soda with buttermilk; mix well.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans greased and floured for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to hard boil, boil 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together in large bowl and drop by spoonful on waxed paper to let cool.
Pack in tin container to stay fresh.

title: sour cream-bean goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and then saute onion, green pepper and garlic powder in that, after you have drained grease.
Add soup.
Stir in beans.
Add Worcestershire sauce, paprika and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes or put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
At the very last, stir in sour cream.

title: philadelphia cream cheese salad (frozen)
directions: Cream cheese should be soft.
Beat the cream stiff, then add the cream cheese and salad dressing to the beaten cream and mix well.
Fold in the marshmallows, pineapple, nuts and cherries. Freeze mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soften at room temperature slightly before serving.

title: pepperoni eggplant crisps
directions: Wash eggplant, slice into 1/2 inch slices. Do not peel. On half of the slices, place mozzarella or jack cheese. Top with 2 or 3 pepperoni slices. Sprinkle with oregano. Top with remaining eggplant halves. Combine bread crumbs and parmesan cheese on a plate. On another plate, place the eggs. Dip the eggplant on each side first in the egg and then in the crumbs. When well-breaded, place on a baking sheet. Drizzle each side with about 1 tsp. of olive oil. Sprinkle with crushed red pepper, if desired. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn with spatula. Bake for 15 minutes on other side. Serve hot, warm, or at room temperature.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix as instructed in sheet pan.
When done, mix together creme of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over sheet cake.
Let cool.
When cake has cooled and absorbed liquid, top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: tennessee lasagna
directions: Cook macaroni; set aside.
Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add sliced Polish sausage and tomatoes.
Cook down a little until sausage is done.
Add macaroni, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: great salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size. Slice onion and fix into rings. Pour dressing over salad.

title: zucchini cornbread(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Place zucchini in a colander. Sprinkle with salt and let drain 10 minutes. Combine all ingredients, except corn meal; add that last. Grease pan well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Stick knife into bread. If it comes out clean, bread is done.

title: lemon-pineapple jello salad
directions: Put canned cream in freezer 1 to 2 hours before making salad. Shake well before adding.
Check halfway to see if it's freezing or not.
(Must be real thick.)
Beat eggs in a cup.
Add to pineapple and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and add Jell-O.

title: sprtiz cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add extract and egg, then flour.
Run through cookie press.
Put on ungreased pans.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not let brown.

title: very best ever french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until oil does not separate from other ingredients.
Put in bottle or jar and store in refrigerator.

title: maple pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together well.
Add 6 egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Reserve whites for later. Sift together flour with soda.
Add to butter mixture, alternating with the sour cream, a little at a time.
Add maple flavoring. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and then pecans.
Bake in greased Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Enjoy!!

title: squash pie
directions: Beat the eggs slightly.
Add salt, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and nutmeg, then the squash.
Mix well.
Pour into the mixture, slowly, the scalded milk.
Line pie plate with pie crust. Pour in the squash mixture.
Bake in slow oven for about 35 minutes.

title: mock potato salad
directions: Cook cauliflower and drain.
Cool.
Add onions, celery and whatever you would add to make regular potato salad (if you add eggs, watch allotment and be sure to add approximate amount of protein to your exchanges).
Use fat-free mayonnaise type salad dressing to mix together.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Serve with Hawaiian bread, wheat or sourdough bread.

title: blue ribbon apple pie
directions: Pare apples.
Slice thin.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Mix with apples.
Place in bottom crust.
Dot with butter. Cover with top crust and crimp to seal.
Cut several slits into top.
Bake in 400° oven 35 to 40 minutes until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 18 to 20 minutes.

title: onion-dill rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids and mix thoroughly.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and form into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: just like "mounds" candy
directions: Mix coconut, nuts and milk together in a large bowl.
Chill 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Shape into small balls.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin in double boiler.
(Can melt chocolate in the microwave on defrost setting.)
Dip balls in melted chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Stir all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with melba toast or cracker bread.

title: bigos(polish hunter's stew)
directions: Combine all ingredients in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, then at 325° for 2 to 3 hours or until veggies are soft.

title: cinnamon spiced pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Place the egg white in a large stainless steel bowl and whisk until frothy.
Slowly whisk in the water, sugar, salt and cinnamon until thick.
Fold in the pecans and toss until well coated.
Transfer pecans to prepared baking sheet and arrange in a single layer.
Place in the oven and bake, stirring every 15 minutes, until the meringue covers the nuts with a chewy, pale golden brown coating, 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from the oven and let sit 5 minutes; then remove the nuts from the pan with a metal spatula and set aside to cool before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, shortening and egg; stir in milk. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Grease
and flour round cake pan.
Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle brown
sugar, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon of sugar on top.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: trash
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake for 1 3/4 hours at 200°.

title: flaky butter pastry
directions: Measure flour into bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix egg with lemon juice and ice water. Sprinkle over flour mixture.
Toss with fork until dough gathers into a ball.
If necessary, add more ice water, 1 tablespoon at a time. Chill to make handling easier.

title: ham and chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Combine all ingredients and put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
This makes enough for at least 10 people.

title: tea cookies
directions: Blend oleo and xxxx sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix in flour; will be stiff.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Roll in xxxx sugar while still warm.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter.
Add flour and milk.
Add drained corn and peppers.
Bake at 350°.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix flour and Crisco until texture of cornmeal.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix, then add rest of ingredients and mix.
Dough will be sticky.
Chill and shape as desired - knots, logs, balls.
Bake and ice when cool.

title: yucky beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion together or combine ham and onion and heat.
Drain beans.
Then combine all ingredients and place in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tis the season biscuit
directions: Mix well!
Roll dough on floured surface and cut into biscuits.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: beef brisket
directions: Pierce meat with fork.
Place on heavy-duty foil.
Pour liquid smoke and Worcestershire over brisket.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap tightly.
Place in pan with tight lid.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in slow 250° oven for 5 to 6 hours.

title: potato cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Roll out size of a marble.
Space apart on cookie sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes at 300°.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: venison roast
directions: Brown roast in oil and put in crock-pot or slow cooker. Season with salt and pepper.
Add cream of celery and French onion soups, water and bell pepper.
Let roast cook overnight.
If desired, potatoes and carrots may be added.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch before serving.

title: campfire beans `n' ham soup
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Cook beans until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, baking cocoa and milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, vanilla, walnuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined trays.
Cool until firm. Yield:
32 servings.

title: beef and cheese log
directions: Mix cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and onion; then roll in beef chips.
Shape into ball or log.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix everything together and chill.

title: lazy-daisy frosting
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Spread on warm cake and place under broiler until slightly browned.
I use this on cakes baked in jelly roll pan.

title: maw maw's banana bread
directions: Mix well at low speed or mix with hands.
Use greased loaf pan.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: italian lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger/sausage, onion, salt and pepper; set aside. Mix spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, minced onion and Italian seasoning; simmer 30 minutes.
Add meat and simmer an extra 30 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, eggs and parsley.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Layer noodles, sauce, meat mixture, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a large baking pan.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls; press with a glass dipped in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place pepper in pot of water and bring to a boil.
Remove.
Slice onion and pepper into six slices.
Put pork chops in baking dish.
To each pork chop, add 1 onion slice, 1 pepper slice and a spoonful of undiluted tomato soup.
(Evenly divide can of soup between the six pork chops.)
Add tiny bit of water to dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for about an hour until meat is done.

title: cherry punch
directions: Mix Cool-Aid, sugar, and pineapple juice.
Pour into water. Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: ellie's pepper relish
directions: Run peppers through a food chopper with onions.
Pour boiling water over them.
Let stand 5 minutes and put in a cloth bag to drain.
Cover with vinegar and add salt and sugar.
Mix well and cook 5 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: peanut bark
directions: Melt chocolate. Add peanut butter, then remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Yields 10 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add Cool Whip and put in crust.
Chill.

title: oven chicken
directions: Mix margarine, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper.
Put chicken in baking dish with bone side up.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pasta fazoola(origin:  italian)
directions: Combine together the oil, salt pork, beans, tomato sauce and celery leaves.
Add seasoning.
Add water and cook 1 hour.
Cook ditalini separate. Drain. Add to soup and simmer 20 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel onions and slice into rings.
Saute in margarine for 15 to 20 minutes until clear.
Put half of onions in a casserole. Top with half of crumbs and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.
You may top with canned onion rings.
A little milk or cream may be added to onions after they have been sauteed or if they are a little dry after baking.

title: fast and easy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: easy fried rice
directions: Fry bacon; break into pieces.
In bacon fat, cook large chopped onion and green pepper.
Add carrots.
Add eggs, scrambling them on one side of the pan.
Add rice.
Fry mixture lightly.

title: jello salad
directions: You also need a jello mold.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter enough potatoes to fill a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, Parmesan cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Roll potatoes in flour mixture and put in baking dish.
Bake in 425° oven about 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Break into bite sized pieces. Return to pot of chicken broth.
Add carrots, celery and onion. Add salt, bouillon cubes and more water, if more broth is needed. Return to boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer for 1 to 2 hours, keeping plenty of broth in pot.
About 10 to 15 minutes before serving, add egg noodles and cook until tender.

title: manicotti with meat stuffing
directions: Saute first three ingredients in the butter or oil.
Drain excess fat and cool.
Add the next 6 ingredients (and the milk if needed).
Stuff the manicotti.
Spoon over a little of the sauce of your choice and bake covered about 40 minutes.
Store overnight.
The next day, spoon over remaining sauce and heat thoroughly.

title: sour cream slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients except cabbage.
Blend well.
Pour over cabbage and toss slightly until well blended.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Use enough whole milk to finish filling gallon container and freeze as usual.

title: crumb pie crust
directions: Mix oil and milk together.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well until all is damp and crumbly.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate, saving 1/2 cup for top of pie.
Fill pie crust with your apple pie recipe.
Sprinkle top of apples with the 1/2 cup crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake for another 50 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: I mix all ingredients together in a pie pan.
Sprinkle pepper on top after spreading.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Use with crackers.

title: orange chicken
directions: Place chicken skin side up in a single layer in a shallow baking pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Blend orange juice, honey, Worcestershire sauce and mustard in a cup; brush part over chicken.
Continue baking, brushing again with remaining orange mixture, 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and richly glazed.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased pan and cook for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: almond-lemonade tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pitcher and stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve over ice.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Beat butter until light and slowly add sugar.
Beat in yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until very fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter in thirds with 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour in three 9-inch buttered pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan, then turn out.

title: garden toss salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Combine all ingredients into large bowl.
Mix together.
Chill for 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Blend all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and chill, then cut into about 4 pieces per tortilla.
Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: green wonders
directions: Mix all ingredients
together in a bowl. Chill 2 hours. Shape into small	balls.	Place
on
cookie
sheet and freeze. When frozen, pack in freezer containers to use as needed. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 250°.
Makes about 70.
Serves about 20.

title: fresh green beans from the garden supper
directions: Place meat in water; add bouillon.
Simmer until meat is nearly cooked; add beans, onion and chopped potatoes.
Add more water if needed.
Cover and cook on simmer until beans are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: santa salad(kids recipe)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and walnuts; stir.
Put half amount in jello mold.
Add sour cream; add rest of jello.
Chill.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased loaf pan at 450° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: seafood and pasta casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease a square casserole dish; place mixture in pan.
Sprinkle extra Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Pick off the bone and place in a large bowl.
Mix chicken with 1 can of cream of chicken soup, milk, precooked noodles and cheese.
Mix with chicken broth, if desired.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed crackers. Pour melted butter evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: creamed green bean salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and combine with green beans. Refrigerate.
Marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly with rice until mixed.
Refrigerate about an hour.
Just before serving, mix in chicken, celery, green pepper and mayonnaise. (Add more mayonnaise, if needed.)
Serve on salad greens.

title: ben's mom's famous fresh fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, pour in blueberries.
Next, layer in sliced strawberries, then the grapes and lastly the chunk pineapple. Set aside.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour with soda.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop level tablespoon of dough on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken oregano
directions: Place chicken in an ungreased baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Garnish with lemon slices (optional).

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and press on a pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese and 8 ounces Cool Whip; spread over cake.
Arrange fruit as desired.

title: mushroom salad(preparation time: 20 minutes plus chilling time)
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms into a large salad bowl. Add cheese and onions. Chill.

title: chicken cacciatore in 20 minutes
directions: Hint:
Can substitute a 16-ounce jar spaghetti sauce plus 1 1/4 cups water.

title: orange glaze for cake
directions: Put sugar and cornstarch in a pan.
Add juice and stir well. Add rest, cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Cool, then spread on any kind of cake.

title: tabouli (lebanese salad)
directions: Soak cracked wheat in water for 20 minutes.
Finely cut up parsley and scallions and tomatoes in bowl.
Drain water from cracked wheat and add to other ingredients.
Add oil, salt, olive oil and juiced lemons.
Best served chilled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french toast
directions: Use a large bowl.
Stir eggs, milk and salt.
Dip both sides of bread.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a skillet; fry bread over medium heat until lightly brown.
Serve with sugar or syrup. Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs into corn.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Blend in milk, cream and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: In saucepan, cook raisins in water until water evaporates. Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Pour into a greased 8 x 8 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat beans for 5 minutes, or until warm.
Spread refried beans in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Add sour cream until beans are covered.
Layer with lettuce, then tomatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: perfect yogurt(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Heat the milk to 176°.
Cover; turn off heat.
Wait 10 minutes.
Turn heat on for 45 seconds.
Turn heat off; wait 10 minutes.
Turn into a heavy casserole dish, a crock-pot or Dutch oven.
Cool milk to between 105° and 115°.
Stir in the yogurt from the store.
It must be the kind with live cultures.
Cover the pot; wrap in 2 bath towels.
Keep at 90° for 3 to 6 hours. Remove towels.
Put yogurt in fridge overnight to set.

title: pineapple filling for cake
directions: Drain pineapple; mix juice with egg yolks, sugar and flour. Cook over low heat or double boiler until mixture starts to thicken.
Add pineapple and cook until thick.
Cool.
Frosts two layer cakes generously.

title: my mom's cheesecake
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan, lined with graham cracker crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all vegetables in small pieces.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put in warm jars with lids.
Place in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
This is a mild salsa.
You can add more peppers to taste.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix and drop onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: bride's hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on bun halves.
Bake in 375° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown and crumble sausage; drain most of fat off.
Add onion and saute lightly.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire, water or V-8, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix well over heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to simmer; cover.
Stir occasionally.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes, until rice is cooked and all liquid is absorbed.
If rice starts to dry out prior to 20 minutes, add more liquid.

title: lois' pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in water with 1/4 teaspoon oil.
Drain in cold water.
Add cheese, vegetables and seasoning to taste.
Mix together and let set in refrigerator for about an hour before serving.
This makes a nice summer salad served on leaf lettuce with bread sticks, fresh cantaloupe and pink lemonade.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add green pepper, refried beans, taco seasoning, onions and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes and put mixture in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with sour cream and Cheddar cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rotel dip
directions: Microwave cheese until melted, stirring frequently. Brown ground beef; drain. Pour melted cheese, ground beef and Ro-Tel tomatoes into crock-pot. Keep crock-pot on medium to high heat. Serve dip over nacho chips.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix drained fruit, sour cream, vanilla and sugar.
Spoon/pour into pie crust.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325 degrees.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Pour boiling water over poppy seed; let stand.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Mix altogether.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.
Watch, burns easily.
Bake in Bundt pan.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine pumpkin pudding mix and pumpkin spice.
Blend with a wire whisk or electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups of the Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, drained pineapple and Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.
In double boiler, heat juice, egg, flour, vinegar and sugar until thick, stirring constantly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix 2 sauces together.
Add apples and peanuts.
Stir and serve.

title: quick dip
directions: Mix well.
Cover, refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Use for chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables, then add green pepper, onion, Miracle Whip and 3/4 cup Velveeta.
Mix together, then top with Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: citrus slaw
directions: In large bowl, whisk together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: cooking for a crowd versatile meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into walnut-sized meatballs. May be made ahead and frozen on cookie sheets, then stored in plastic bags until ready to use.
There is no end to the variety of dishes that can be made with these little meatballs.
Makes about 80.

title: belle's squash
directions: Cook squash in small amount of salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add cracker crumbs, milk, eggs, onion and cheese. Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: surprise chicken
directions: Mix all together except chicken.
Pour over chicken that has been placed in a greased baking dish.
Cook, covered with foil, for 2 hours at 350°.

title: dried beef and cheese pie
directions: Thin cream cheese with milk. Add next 4 ingredients and place in an 8-inch pyrex pie plate.

title: abbey's texas tatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Boil potatoes until tender.
Place potatoes into
a casserole dish. Coat the potatoes with sour cream.
Slice cheese and place over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: fish stew
directions: Fry fat back. Fry onions in fat back grease. Combine rest of ingredients and cook about 6 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Spread on cake while warm.
This is very good.

title: steele pizza
directions: Take the Boboli crust and spread the Brie cheese on it. Sprinkle
on the brown sugar so the pizza is covered. Then add some almonds. Put under the broiler until the top starts to get brown and bubbly. Take it out and cut into slices. Enjoy.

title: cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle sides of a 9-inch buttered spring-form pan with 2 tablespoons of the crumbs. Mix together remaining crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar. Pack into bottom of pan.

title: key lime pie(easy)
directions: Mix cream cheese and condensed milk.
Then add limeade.
Add food coloring to suit.
Fold mixture into Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts.
Freeze 24 hours.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Cream together the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Add the apples and nuts.
Mix well and put into large tube pan.
Bake 70 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan or spray with nonstick vegetable oil.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Line bottom and partially up the sides of the prepared pan.
Refrigerate until ready to add filling.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Simmer cucumber slices in 4 cups vinegar with salt, mustard seed and 1/4 cup sugar until slices turn slightly yellow (about 15 minutes).
Cook in covered pot.
Do not overcook.
Drain; discard liquid.
Spoon slices into hot, sterilized jars.
Bring to boil 3 1/3 cups vinegar, 5 3/4 cups sugar, celery seed and allspice. Pour over pickles.
Seal at once and process in boiling water bath in canner 5 minutes.
Remove jars.
Makes 5 pints.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups of flour and next 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well and set aside.
Heat milk and water in a heavy saucepan until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients, stirring well.
Stir in remaining 3 cups of flour to form a soft dough.
Divide into 3 equal portions.
Place 1 portion in each of 3 (13 ounce) coffee cans coated with cooking spray and sprinkled with 3/4 teaspoon cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) for 45 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove; cool.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
If sauce is too thick, add milk until it is of desired consistency.

title: apple cake
directions: Soften margarine and mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
The apples should be peeled and chopped into 1/4 to 1/2-inch chunks.
Use 2 large loaf, 5 small loaf or 1 tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Can be served with Cool Whip.

title: crock-pot pork roast
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Bake and enjoy.

title: candy cookies
directions: Melt the almond bark and peanut butter together in microwave or in double boiler.
Stir together and cool until room temperature.
Add the Rice Krispies, nuts and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon (or size you prefer) onto waxed paper.
Allow to stand to harden.

title: sweet potatoes in maple syrup
directions: Bake sweet potatoes (pierce skin) at 375° about 45 minutes until tender. Slip off skins. Cut potatoes into half inch pieces. Cook remaining ingredients in skillet about 6 minutes or until apple is tender. Add sweet potatoes. Mix carefully until coated.

title: red cabbage with apples
directions: Combine cabbage and water; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Add the apples, butter or margarine, vinegar, flour, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add all other ingredients and stir in well.
Refrigerate until set firm.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook ground beef with onion. Layer cabbage on bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix ground meat with rice. Pour rice mixture on top of cabbage. Add tomato soup with can of water and top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, chiles, garlic and peppers in oil until soft. Add tomatoes, consomme, broth, water, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and steak sauce.
Bring soup to a boil, lower heat to simmer and cook, covered, for 1 hour.
Add tortillas and cheese and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: spinach salad
directions: Chop spinach and scallions and egg together, mix with mayonnaise.
Place mixture on a bed of lettuce, garnish with tomatoes.

title: sweet-sour potatoes
directions: Peel and slice or dice potatoes.
Cook in salted water until done.
Fry bacon crisp and set aside.
In bacon grease, add 1 cup sugar and 3/4 cup vinegar.
Bring to boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add a thickening of cornstarch.
While potatoes are hot, add 1 small onion and the sauce, stirring well.
Add bacon (crumbled).
Serve warm.

title: sunday morning sandwiches
directions: Lightly coat the cut side of each bun with 1 1/2 teaspoons margarine per side. Place on griddle and brown; set aside.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Season chicken well.
Boil until tender, cook and cut into bite size pieces.
Melt butter; add flour and stir into mixture. Add milk and cook until sauce is thick and creamy.
Add cut up chicken, pimentos, mushrooms, parsley and sherry.
Season to taste and serve hot in patty shells or on toast.

title: english date pudding
directions: Dissolve brown sugar in water.
Pour into baking dish.
Add batter made up of the remaining ingredients.
Do not stir batter into syrup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, then egg and cream well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll into sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cookies will crack on top when done.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Combine cornmeal and baking soda in medium bowl.
Add buttermilk, egg and 1 tablespoon melted shortening.
Stir just until moistened.
Heat 1/4 cup shortening on medium-high heat in large, heavy skillet.
Pour 1/4 cut batter into skillet for each hoe cake.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown on each side. Add additional shortening, if necessary.
Drain on paper towel. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and put into a loaf pan. Spread about 1 Tbsp. of ketchup on top.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender; bone and cut in pieces.
Drop noodles in boiling water and cook until tender, then drain.
Cook onion, pepper and celery in chicken broth until tender.
Thicken rest of broth with flour.
Mix chicken, noodles and cooked vegetables together, then add mushroom soup and 3/4 of the cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix enough of the broth to keep from being dry. Bake in well-greased casserole dish at 350° for about 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese just before serving.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Drain, flake salmon; reserve liquid.
Place rice in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with kernel corn including juice. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Layer half of the stewed tomatoes over corn, then layer mushrooms, flaked salmon and top with the remaining tomatoes.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes. Garnish with green pepper rings.
Serves 6.

title: roast rock cornish hens
directions: Thaw Cornish hens overnight in refrigerator.

title: one-hour rolls
directions: Mix milk, salt and shortening and sugar to a boil; dissolve yeast cake in warm milk mixture.
Let milk cool until just warm. Add beaten egg and dissolve yeast cake mixture with flour.
Pour in greased mixing bowl.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature. Knead about 8 or 9 times.
Roll out and make into desired shapes. Let stand another hour if permissible or else maybe bake right away.
Always best to let stand another hour.
Bake at 450°.

title: country brownies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and syrup. Fold in nuts.
Grease and flour a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Top with icing, if desired.

title: caramel apple cookie pizza
directions: Soak apple slices in lemon juice to prevent browning; set aside.
Press cookie dough into a 12 inch pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Remove from oven and let cool. Combine cream cheese and peanut butter, spread onto cooled crust. Arrange apple slices on top.
Drizzle with caramel topping and sprinkle with nuts.

title: kick the can ice cream
directions: You will need one 13 ounce (1 pound) coffee can and one 39 ounce (3 pound) coffee can.

title: shaun's chicken
directions: Stew chicken 15 minutes.
Cool.
Break into bite size pieces. Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken, soup and sour cream into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and slices of butter.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Cut up all ingredients, except gelatin, and puree in food processor.
Drain off juice.
Heat gelatin in double boiler.
Add to puree.
Add mayonnaise to vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate overnight.
Spread on thin brown bread slices. Cut into thirds and store in plastic container.
These can be made the night before.
Makes 16 whole sandwiches if the crust is cut off before spreading.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Mix in cheese and milk until completely melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Blend pineapple, milk and margarine. Crumble in bread and eggs. Add sugar. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Brush top with 1 tablespoon milk after done.

title: 49'ers
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans to mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: In medium size bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk and stir until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with chilled cherry pie filling before serving.

title: lumberjacks
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses and unbeaten eggs. Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into beaten ingredients and thoroughly mix.
Put 1/4 cup of sugar in a small bowl.
Pinch off a ball of dough the size of a walnut; roll into a ball and dip it into the sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen large soft cookies.
Great with cold milk!

title: gayle's oat bran applesauce muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Combine wheat flour, oat bran, fructose, wheat germ, soda, baking powder, salt, cloves, nutmeg, allspice and cinnamon together.
Mix butter, oil, applesauce, buttermilk, egg and vanilla in mixture well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fill greased and floured muffin tins (paper cupcake liners may be used in muffin tins).
Also, if you don't have muffin tins, place cupcake liners in a 2-inch deep pan before filling.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
May be frozen.

title: oatmeal shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. In mixing bowl, cream together the butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, flour and salt and mix together.
