Use your hands if you have to; spoon mixture into prepared pan and press down firmly.
Bake about 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven.
Cut into squares.

title: oven-fried parmesan chicken
directions: In a large shallow dish, combine melted butter with garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
In plastic bag, combine bread crumbs with remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces in butter mixture and then shake in plastic bag, coating well.
Arrange pieces in another large shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining butter over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and done.

title: molasses cake
directions: Beat all together; add enough flour to make a batter and bake.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend all but 3/4 cup cake mix, oleo and egg.
Press into greased and floured 9x13 pan.

Set aside. Mix pumpkin, 3 eggs, brown sugar, evaporated milk, cinnamon and sugar together and pour over the mix in the pan. With the remaining 3/4 cup dry mix, add 1/2 cup sugar. Work together with hands. Add 1/4 stick melted oleo.
Mix well and sprinkle over the pumpkin mix.
Sprinkle some sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: yum-yum chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix chicken soup and sour cream together. Pour over chicken. Crush Ritz crackers. Stir in poppy seed and melted butter. Spread on top of chicken. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and drain.
Top each with a slice of apple and orange.
Sprinkle with dash of cinnamon and cloves. Add beef broth (undiluted) and brown sugar.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir cornstarch into orange juice until smooth.
Blend into broth. Simmer a few minutes until sauce is thickened.
Remove chops to platter and pour sauce over them.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine cranberries, water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook until berries pop (about 5 minutes).
Remove from burner and add orange marmalade and pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: tapioca salad
directions: When water boils, add tapioca.
Keep water boiling rapidly. Do not drain.
When tapioca is clear (about 15 minutes), add jello and sugar.
When cool and thickened, stir in whipped topping. Fruits are optional.
If using strawberry jello, use strawberries. If using raspberry jello, use raspberries.

title: judy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Beat oleo, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat in flour and baking soda to form dough. Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Slowly brown roast in Wesson oil in preheated kettle.
Combine mustard, brown sugar, vinegar, pepper and water in small bowl. Pour over roast.
Cover and simmer slowly for 4 hours or until tender.

title: cafe calypso
directions: Take a handful of bits of root for every half gallon of tea. Boil as you would coffee.
If you like strong flavor, boil until water turns darkish red.
Sweeten as you like.
Don't throw the roots away.
They'll last for several makings.
(Choose roots that are red and clean and soak overnight.)

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano and garlic salt. Dip chicken in melted butter; roll in crumb mixture.
Place in 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
To the leftover butter, add onion, parsley and wine.
Pour over baked chicken and bake 10 minutes more.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Using small amount of scalded milk, make a paste of sugar mixture.
Add this to the rest of the milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil for about 1 minute.
Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in oleo and vanilla.
In a large bowl, arrange vanilla wafers on bottom and sides.
Slice banana onto wafers.
Pour pudding mixture to cover.
Then layer wafers, bananas and pudding to top of bowl.
May top with meringue if you wish.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk. Add eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix. Add butter and mix. Sprinkle in cinnamon and mix. Pour in buttered 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle more cinnamon on top of pudding. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: confetti cabbage
directions: Melt margarine.
Add vegetables. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes. Shaking pan, season and cook another minute. Serve.

title: strawberry kiwi jam
directions: Rinse and pat dry strawberries.
Place in medium bowl; crush with a potato masher.
Combine strawberries, kiwi, lemon juice, ginger and pectin in a large saucepot.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring frequently.
Add sugar; return to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 1 minute if using Sure-Jell pectin or 4 minutes if using MCP pectin.
Remove from heat; skim foam, if necessary, or place 1 teaspoon of butter to cut foaming down.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in simmering water bath.
Makes 6 half-pint jars.

title: pastor diane's powerful punch
directions: Add 1 can of each juice and fill punch bowl with lemon-lime soda.
Scoop sherbet to float on top.
Serves 20 to 30 people and fills 2 large punch bowls.

title: auntie el's cheese ball
directions: Mix together except walnuts.
Form ball and top with walnuts.

title: double cocoa lovers zucchini cake(perry county 3rd place hershey's greatest cocoa cake contest)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch pans (round).
Grate enough zucchini to equal three cups.
In large mixer at medium, beat salad oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually add melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fold in shredded zucchini, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour. Cool and frost.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Let sauerkraut and sugar stand 1/2 hour, covered in refrigerator.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mulligatawny
directions: Melt butter in the pot in which soup will be made.
Add onion and crushed garlic; cook over low heat until the onion is soft. Remove garlic; add flour and curry powder.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add milk and chicken stock which have been cooked over hot water until smooth.
Add apple, peeled and chopped, 10 minutes before serving. Season with salt and freshly ground pepper (just a dash).
Serves 6.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Crush crackers and mix with 1 stick of butter, softened.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream other 2 sticks of butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs for 20 minutes.
Spread over graham crackers. Slice bananas lengthwise and place on top.
Drain pineapple well and place on bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add to baked, cooled pie crusts.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage corn chowder
directions: Brown sausage. Drain. Add onions. Cook 1 minute. Place in crock-pot, adding other ingredients. Place cheese on each serving.

title: baked chicken
directions: Bone chicken breasts.
Line pan with dried beef.
Wrap chicken in bacon and place on beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 minutes, then at 250° until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: potato and green bean salad
directions: Wash potatoes and boil in jackets.
Fry bacon and crumble, reserving grease.
Chop onions, also use blades of onions and chop pimentos.
Heat and drain green beans. Peel and slice potatoes in a large bowl. Add crumbled bacon, green onions, pimentos and green beans.
To grease, add the vinegar and sugar. Heat and pour over vegetables. Salt and pepper to taste. Toss.
Serve warm.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour oil and water into 1 cup measuring cup (do not stir).
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until mixture comes away from sides of bowl.
Form into 2 balls and roll between 2 (12-inch) squares of waxed paper.
(Dampen the area to prevent paper slippage.)
Crust is correct thickness when it reaches edge of paper.
Peel off top sheet of waxed paper and fit dough, paper side up, into pie plate.
Remove paper. Finish pie shell following single or double-crust pies.
Makes pastry for 8 or 9-inch double crust pie.
Single crust:
Prick bottom and sides well with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth chicken
directions: Boil, skin and debone chicken; cut into bite size pieces. Place in casserole dish and pour chicken broth on top. Combine flour, butter, water and buttermilk. Pour over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eagle brand dessert
directions: Pour all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Garnish top with nuts and sliced maraschino cherries.

title: slender potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and water in microwavable 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 9 minutes.
Stir once during cycle.
Stir in remaining ingredients except for cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook, uncovered, on Medium-high 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted and potatoes are tender.

title: nachos
directions: Put melted cheese on top of microwave.
Cheese heats up and heat up chips.
Put them in refrigerator until they are all gone. Then we enjoy them.

title: winning tea punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine instant tea, water, concentrates and cranberry juice.
Just before serving, add ice.
Makes more than 1 gallon or 25 (5-ounce) servings.

title: quick rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm water and mix.
Add sugar, salt, egg and shortening and mix.
Add 1/2 flour and mix.
Add rest of flour and mix.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise in warm place about 1 hour to double in bulk.
Pan rolls and let rise in warm place about 1 hour.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Spray with Pam or brush with melted butter.
Dough can be made the night before and placed in refrigerator for use the next day.

title: hot crab meat appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine all ingredients except almonds. Blend well.
Spread in ovenproof dish and top with almonds.
Bake until hot.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugars and water.
Stir constantly until it reaches 300° on candy thermometer or when dropped in cold water it hardens immediately.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg well; add milk, then add to the dry ingredients.
Add melted butter; place in a shallow pan and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: polynesian rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in butter.
Cook rice in broth from the chicken.
Mix all ingredients together, except the almonds.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Brown the almonds in butter.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.
Allow to cool.

title: long loaf bread
directions: Mix 1 c. scalded milk with oleo, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water, not hot water.
Let yeast set until it rises.
When milk mixture is cool, add yeast and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Let stand until light, then add 1 or 1 1/2 cups more flour.
Mix to a stiff dough and let stand until light.
Mix down again.
When light, roll out like cookie dough, then roll up and place on greased cookie sheet, corner ways.
When double in size, bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs.
Dip chicken into melted margarine. Roll in Ritz cracker crumbs.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and pour into buttered casserole dish, about 13 x 9. Saute onions, garlic and celery in oleo. Add Cheez Whiz or Cheddar cheese soup and broccoli. Stir carefully and pour over rice and mix lightly. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, soup mix and egg and form into tiny meatballs. Brown in skillet.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon of fat.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix and Cool Whip; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and chill.
Add the last 3 ingredients according to your own
taste.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie cloves, allspice and cinnamon in cheesecloth; place in a large kettle or crock-pot with cider and sugar.
Simmer.
Serve with a lemon slice in each serving.
Makes 16 servings.

title: tea cakes(1860)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, nutmeg and vanilla. Mix well.
Roll, cut and bake at 375°.

title: chicken broccoli muffins
directions: Poach chicken in just enough water to cover, about 15 minutes or until cooked through.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat 6 cups of a standard muffin tin with nonstick baking spray.
Put all ingredients in food processor and process until pureed.
Spoon an equal amount of chicken mixture into each cup.
Bake 40 minutes or until firm to touch.
Unmold and serve when cool enough to eat or refrigerate and serve cold.

title: corn dressing
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix corn, oil and cheese and onion.
Mix well. Add to corn meal.
Pour in oiled 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Mix and let stand 30 minutes.
Cook 30 minutes, stirring often until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in one box of strawberry jello.
Seal in hot jars.
When cool, keep refrigerated.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Mix apples, applesauce, Equal and cornstarch together.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with margarine. Add top crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Scoop
out sherbet into punch bowl.
Slowly add 7-Up, stirring constantly.
Serve and enjoy.

title: island salad dressing
directions: Put all in jar; shake and chill.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Melt baking chocolate and add to batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hearty cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
In a double boiler, melt oleo and add flour gradually to avoid lumps.
Gradually add 4 cups milk, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and let melt.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Makes about 8 cups.
Fits perfectly in a lettuce keeper.

title: herbed burgers
directions: Mix together and form patties.
If desired, freeze in individual sandwich bags to be used as needed.

title: beef on a stick
directions: Combine seven ingredients in shallow dish; add steak and stir to coat the meat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Remove from marinade and thread on 6 skewers.
You may add chunks of green pepper, onion and tomato between the chunks of steak. Place on grill over hot coals.
Turn every three or four minutes until done.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain off grease.
Add all remaining ingredients into a soup pot or Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil and lower heat and let simmer 10 minutes.
Garnish with shredded cheese and Fritos.
May want to add water to make more soupy.

title: heather's chocolate cake with fresh raspberries
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch spring-form pan.
Pour boiling water over chocolate and butter.
When melted, stir in vanilla and sugar, then whisk in egg yolks one at a time. Mix baking soda and sour cream and whisk into chocolate mixture. Sift flour and baking powder together; add to batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir a quarter of the egg whites into batter. Fold remaining egg whites into the batter.
Pour batter into pan. Place on middle rack in oven and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until cake tester inserted into the middle comes out clean.
Cool; remove from pan.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in that order!

title: coconut custard
directions: Combine.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peachy grilled chicken
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin and peach; mix well. Set aside 1 cup for serving.
Grill chicken, uncovered, over medium heat for 3 minutes on each side.
Baste with some of the remaining peach sauce.
Continue grilling for 6 to 8 minutes or until meat juices run clear, basting and turning several times. Serve with reserved peach sauce.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: carrot cake and frosting
directions: Combine together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add vegetable oil.
Add eggs, beating in one egg at a time.
Add carrots.
Stir in vanilla and chopped nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 10-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish.
Brown sausage and onion; drain well.

title: black bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let simmer 45 minutes to an hour.
Can serve with nacho chips.

title: cabbage roll
directions: Cook cabbage leaves for 2 minutes in enough water to cover; drain off water and set aside. Mix other ingredients. Place mixture on cabbage leaf and roll. Wrap in foil. Place in 300° oven for 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving liquid.
Drain orange slices, reserving liquid. Drain cherries.

Place all fruit (except bananas) in serving bowl. Combine 2 cups pineapple liquid with vanilla pudding (use orange slice juice if there isn't enough pineapple juice). Cook over medium heat until thickened and transparent.
Pour over fruit in serving bowl.
Chill. Add sliced bananas right before serving.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Whish in flour and cook 3-4 minutes until the flour is the color of straw.
Add onion celery and bell pepper; mix and simmer for 4-5 minutes.
Add stock, blend with vegetables and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Add milk and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer 15-20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Edges should be slightly browned.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin and cool.
Peel potatoes and shred coarsely.
In a saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and butter until melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions and seasoning.
Fold into potatoes and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding apples last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole and cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Put half of Jell-O mixture in container.
Let jell.
Add sour cream.
Pour remaining Jell-O over sour cream and let jell.

title: vegetable-orange(orange-winter squash-carrot)
directions: Combine carrots and squash; microwave, boil or steam until tender.
Add orange pieces and warm 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with pinch of nutmeg.
Serves 4.

title: midnight french toast
directions: Mix eggs, cream, vanilla, orange zest and liqueur in large pan with cover.
Place sliced bread in pan, making sure slices are well coated.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning, place slices on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with fruit or maple syrup.
Serves 6.

title: merry christmas grog
directions: Pierce pears twice with fork.
Wrap each pear in waxed paper. Twist ends to seal.
Microwave on High 4 minutes or until tender. Set aside still wrapped.

title: sugar free banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk until thickened.
Line bottom of medium baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Spread a layer of pudding mix over wafers.
Slice a layer of bananas over mix.
Layer another layer of wafers and top with pudding and bananas, top with cool whip.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: superior vanilla, butter and nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly, then mix soda and salt with buttermilk until foamy, adding alternately with the flour to first mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Add the flavoring and egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put in pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.
This cake is delicious, tender and fine textured.

title: beef saute "for two"
directions: Saute beef, macaroni, onion and green pepper in hot oil until macaroni turns slightly yellow.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomato juice and rest of seasonings.
Bring to a slow boil.
Turn to "simmer."
Cover and simmer on low.
Check so it doesn't stick at 15 minutes.
Can be served from pan or cut down on simmer time and put in oven with a crumb topping and heated until ready.
Bon appetit.

title: cauliflower pie
directions: Press crescent rolls into 9-inch pie pan like a pie crust. Cook cauliflower a little and drain good.
Melt butter and pour over cauliflower.
Put buttered cauliflower on crescent roll crust.
Chop up an onion over cauliflower.
Beat eggs and pour on top of mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Make this in layers in a glass dish.
1st layer:
Spread warm beans evenly in dish.
2nd layer:
Spread taco sauce.
3rd layer: Combine sour cream and taco seasoning (use as much as you want--more makes it spicier).
Spread this over the taco sauce. 4th layer:
sprinkle cheese over taco sauce.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cappuccino
directions: Mix and boil.
Top off with whipped cream.

title: pound cake(this was my mother's recipe)
directions: Grease and flour a round cake pan.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Wash the chicken, then put in a pan.
Add garlic and all the other ingredients.
Cover and cook for 1/2 hour or until chicken is tender.
Put over steamed rice to eat.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Toss potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onion together; turn into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper. Top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
It should be somewhat bubbly.
Makes 12 servings (contains 29.5 grams fat per serving).

title: beef tenderloin cooked new way
directions: Sprinkle lemon pepper on all sides of tenderloin.
Set oven temperature at 500° (not broiler).
When temperature light goes out, put tenderloin in heavy baking pan.
Bake 4 minutes per pound.
Shut oven off.
Leave meat in oven for 2 hours.
Do not open oven door until 2 hours are up.
Tenderloin will be medium-rare!

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cut a chicken for frying and fry out bacon slices.
Remove bacon.
Dredge chicken with flour; saute in bacon grease.
Put 2 quarts cold water in soup kettle with sliced okra, tomatoes, corn, potatoes (cubed) and diced onion.
Boil all together until done. Pour 1 quart boiling water over chicken and boil until meat falls off bone.
Remove chicken; chop fine and add water in which it was cooked and chopped chicken to the vegetables.
Thicken, season and serve.

title: egg nog cake
directions: Cream oleo with 3 cups confectioners sugar.
Add egg yolks. Add brandy, vanilla, nutmeg and walnuts.
Ice between cake layers and refrigerate.

title: tomato ketchup(for canning)
directions: Wash, trim and cut the tomatoes.
Add the onion and celery. Cook until all is tender.
Put through colander or Foley's mill. Add the vinegar, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, dry mustard, salt and sugar.
Cook until thick.
A little clear gel may be added to help thicken.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook and stir beef in shortening until beef is brown, about 15 minutes. In slow cooker, add beef, 3 cups water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Cook for 3 hours, then add vegetables, bouquet sauce, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, bouillon cube and bay leaf. Continue to cook until vegetables are tender, about 2 hours. When vegetables are done, shake flour and cold water in container. Stir gradually into stew.

title: layered low-fat banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place banana slices on this.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add milk, mix.
Add pudding mixes. Mix until smooth and well blended.
Spread over banana slices. Spoon pineapple on top.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple. Garnish with extra banana, if desired.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Keep unused portions refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix soups and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Crush crackers.
Mix with margarine and sprinkle on top of soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly.

title: cheese souffle with peppers
directions: Process cheese and peppers together.
Generously butter a bread or casserole pan.
Put in a layer of bread and then cheese and peppers.
Continue layers until dish is full.
Add milk and eggs mixed together.
Bake in 350° for 1 hour.
This recipe came from a good friend who was an excellent cook.

title: divinity drops
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Sift sugar.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add the sugar very slowly, whipping constantly.
Add vanilla and lemon peel.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Drop the batter from a spoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet and shape into cones.
Bake until the drops are partly dry and hold their shape, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from sheet while still hot.
Allow to cool.
Makes about 45 cookies.
Contains 31 calories per cookie; 23% cal. from fat, 1 gram fat, 0 cholesterol, 0 grams protein, 6 grams carbohydrates and 2 mg. sodium.

title: great marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate for 3 hours or longer. Great for lamb, beef or chicken.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line cookie sheet with wax paper; grease well.
Mix all ingredients; pour onto cookie sheet.
Spread evenly.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out; sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Flip onto towel.
Roll up towel like a jelly roll.
Cool; unroll and spread with filling and roll back.

title: toasted pecan candy
directions: Toast pecans and oleo at 350° for 15 minutes; stir frequently. Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add pecans.
Add the vanilla and powdered sugar; beat well.
Pour into Pyrex.
This freezes well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line a 13x9 inch pyrex dish with whole crackers. Cut up 1/2 stick of oleo and place on top.
Layer chicken next.
Mix sour cream and soups and pour over chicken.

Crush 1 stack of Ritz crackers (more if needed). Sprinkle over casserole. Cut up 1/2 stick of Oleo and place over the top of crackers. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350 degrees until bubbly. This casserole is even better if refrigerated over night.

title: marshmallow cream pineapple cake
directions: Make cake as directed and bake.
Once cake is done and while it is still hot, in saucepan heat pineapple with juice and 1 cup sugar and bring to a rolling boil.
Punch holes in cake with fork and pour pineapple liquid over cake.
Spoon marshmallow cream over cake like icing.
Take remaining pineapple and place over marshmallow cream.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts; spread over bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan. Prepare cake mix according to package instructions. Pour mixture over nuts and coconut. Mix together melted butter, sugar and cream cheese; spread over cake mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together and stir into the butter mixture the dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Add warm applesauce last.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: southern delight
directions: Cut up angel food cake into small pieces.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chopped or cut up fruit.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Layer on top of fruit.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon meringue cake with strawberries
directions: Mix strawberries and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Beat flour, 1 cup of sugar, the margarine, milk, baking powder, lemon peel, salt and 2 egg whites or egg substitute in large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from oven.

title: squash fritters
directions: Pour oil in pan; put burner on low.
Grate squash on coarse part of grater.
Turn stove burner up to 3 and add the dry ingredients and egg quickly and start frying.
The longer squash sets after grated, the more liquid they get.

title: chicken 'n broccoli casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread out broccoli and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay chicken breasts over broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and almond slivers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: pepperoni surprise
directions: Slice pepperoni.
Cook egg noodles for 8 minutes; drain.
Mix noodles, pepperoni, tomatoes and 1/4 package of cheese on low to medium heat until mixed together.
Pour into a square baking pan. Spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown and cheese is melted.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Separate crescent rolls, slice apple in 16 pieces.
Roll apples in crescent rolls starting with one side.
Layer in 9 x 13 pan.
Melt butter, mix with sugar, and cinnamon.
Pour over crescent rolls.
Pour can of Mountain Dew over rolls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: skewered chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips 1 1/2-inches wide and 1/2-inch thick. Thread strips loosely onto 6 to 8 skewers.
Place skewers in two layers in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours. Drain.
Grill over hot coals 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Serves six.

title: walking tostitos
directions: Spread and layer each of the first three ingredients in a 12 to 14-inch shallow platter in order listed; sprinkle the next 4 ingredients over the top in the order listed.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours; remove and let stand for about 20 minutes before serving.
Garnish edges of the platter with a layer of chips, dipped in the mixture.
Serve remaining chips in a basket.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until golden.
Cool in pan. Sift confectioners sugar over cool cake, if desired.
This makes a delicious cake on the consistency of pound cake.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove the chicken from the bone. In a large bowl, mix together the chicken, tomatoes, mushrooms and black olives.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add mayonnaise until the consistency is right for you.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Melt the chocolate chips in medium saucepan over low heat; remove.
Stir in liqueur and frosting; blend well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours until firm.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together white sugar, brown sugar, shortening and margarine.
Whip in eggs; then add flour, oats, baking powder and chocolate chips.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter 'n syrup
directions: Spoon three heaping Tbsp. of your favorite smooth peanut butter in to a small bowl.
Add four Tbsp. of Griffin's Waffle Syrup and stir until smooth.
Spread on bread or toast and top with another slice.
So easy...kids can fix their own snack!

title: gradys cheese toast
directions: Shred and mix cheeses.
Slice bun lengthwise and butter. Sprinkle on cheese.
Broil until melted.

title: chuck wagon casserole(makes six 1-cup servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crumble ground meat into a medium skillet.
Brown over medium heat; drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat with salt.
In a 2-quart casserole, stir chili beans with gravy, hominy and soup until combined.
Stir in meat.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until heated through.
Arrange cheese on top.
Bake 2 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: german coffee cake
directions: Cool scalded milk to lukewarm, then add to the yeast that has been dissolved in the 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt and melted oleo.
Beat in the 2 1/4 cups flour; beat until your arm gets tired.
Ha!
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.

title: potato, carrot and onion roast
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, carrots, onion, oil, salt and pepper.
Toss to coat.
Transfer potato mixture to roasting pan.
Bake until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: You will also need a candy thermometer.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, powdered sugar, butter and oil; add egg, vanilla, soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Roll in balls the size of walnut.
Roll in sugar before baking (optional).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Let this start to jell.
Drain pineapple (save juice); add pineapple, sliced bananas and marshmallows to Jell-O.
Let stand until firm.
Cook 1 cup pineapple juice, 1 beaten egg, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Cook until thick; let cool, then spread on Jell-O.
Whip together the packages of Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Spread over layer.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Add garlic, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, basil, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until thick. Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs, remaining parsley flakes and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Grate Mozzarella, American, Colby, Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half the cheese mixture over noodles.
Spread half the grated cheeses over the cheese mixture; cover with half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade minestrone
directions: Cook beans, salt, garlic, pepper, oil, butter, water and tomatoes over low flame, stir.
Prepare vegetables and add to pot. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add wine and pasta.
Simmer 10 or 15 minutes.
Serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: crunchy fudge sandwich
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels with peanut butter in a heavy saucepan, stirring until blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press half of mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: homemade mincemeat
directions: Cook beef well.
Drain.
Grind suet raw.
Grind cooked beef. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Thin with apple juice or water.
Can mincemeat.
Makes 12 quarts.
1 quart makes 2 pies.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Make a roux with the oil and flour.
When golden brown, add the onions.
Add tomato paste; saute slowly for 10 minutes.
Add the bell pepper, shallots, shrimp, parsley, salt, pepper, Tony's seasoning and Tabasco.
Simmer 5 more minutes, then add tomatoes, corn, chicken broth and bay leaf.
If too thick, water can be added.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: fiesta corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a lightly oiled 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except steak; mix well.
Score flank steak on both sides.
Place in glass baking dish; pour marinade over all.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours; turn once.
Barbecue or broil steak 6 inches from heat, about 5 minutes on each side, to desired doneness; baste occasionally with marinade.
To serve, slice thinly across grain.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine brown sugar and oil.
Stir in egg, buttermilk, salt, soda, vanilla and flour; mix well.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Done when toothpicks come out clean.
Cool and serve with margarine, cream cheese or Cool Whip.
(May be frozen for 6 months.)

title: cookies
directions: Mix and drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. We like them plain, but you may frost with powdered sugar or cream cheese frosting.

title: scallops en brochette
directions: Wash and pat scallops dry.
On each of 4 skewers, intertwine a strip of bacon with 4 to 6 scallops until bacon and scallops are used up.
Brush the scallops with melted margarine and parsley. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turkey cobb salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, egg and diced turkey. Sprinkle on shredded cheese and top with your favorite salad dressing.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Do not beat until frothy.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake about 50 more minutes.
May cover with foil last 20 minutes to keep crust from burning.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 9 cups.
This will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook sugar, vanilla, eggs, butter and chopped dates for 7 minutes.
Set off stove and let cool.
After cool, add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls and roll into coconut.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: bean and meat stew
directions: Fry hamburger and onions.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Simmer in electric frypan for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: fried plantains
directions: Peel and slice plantains.
Deep fry in oil.
Remove.
Coat with sugar, if desired.

title: sour cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and boil with sugar.
Add jello, water and juice of orange and lemon, grated rind of both and pineapple.
Cool.
Mix with cherries and pecans.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, mixing well. Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add soda and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into 3 layer pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan which have been greased and floured or lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: minihaha cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites stiff.
Put yolks in with whites and beat until well mixed.
Add margarine and sugar; beat well. Add vanilla and baking powder.
Add alternately flour and milk, while mixing.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Doesn't even need frosting.

title: pork chalupas
directions: Combine ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water and simmer 6 hours, stirring and adding water, as needed.
Remove meat and shred.
Cook another 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over chips or rice or in flour tortillas.

title: wetback special
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1 hour, stirring often.
Serve over regular Fritos.
Top with grated cheese, chopped tomatoes, lettuce, onion, green pepper, sour cream and taco sauce as desired.
A delicious, make-it-yourself Mexican meal.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 stick of margarine in casserole dish. Layer cabbage, onions and then cheese.
Mix in a bowl the mayonnaise and cream of mushroom.
Then spread over top of cheese.
Mix crackers and the rest of the margarine together; put on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Cover with aluminum foil the first 30 minutes.

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine butter and eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: cool summer salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to package directions. Drain. Add Veg-All, tuna, onions, cheese and pickles. Mix sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, seasoned salt and seasoned pepper. Toss with macaroni mixture. CHILL. Serves 6 to 8.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole except rice and soup; cover with Cheddar soup.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve with wild rice.
Serves 4.

title: irvin cobb's milk punch
directions: Mix sugar and bourbon with milk and pour into container with cracked ice; mix well for additional chill.
Strain into drinking glass or mug and sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems.
Mound with cream cheese.
Place in baking pan with butter.
Sprinkle with green chilies and seasoned salt.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding ala wally troop
directions: Mix in a large bowl the vanilla pudding and milk.
Fold in sour cream and 1 container Cool Whip.
Line flat-type container with vanilla wafers.
Layer bananas, mixture and wafers until to the top of the container. Top with the remaining container of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with crushed vanilla wafers and red maraschino cherries.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Arrange a layer of half buttered crumbs in bottom of a 9-inch round, shallow baking dish.
Pour oysters and their liquid over crumbs in a uniform layer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with remaining crumbs and pour milk over all.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Yields 5 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Lightly cook onion in shortening or butter until tender.
Add hamburger; cook until done.
Mix hamburger mixture and other ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vequenos(cheese snacks)
directions: Put 1 cup flour and shortening in large bowl.
Add egg and mix together.
Add sugar and salt to water, then add second cup flour. Mix thoroughly and chill about 1 hour before rolling.
Cut cheese into sticks about 3 x 1/2-inch.
When dough is easily handled, roll on floured surface, then cut into strips about 1/2-inch wide. Wind strips around cheese as if binding a finger.
Be careful to cover cheese completely.
Pinch ends together.
Put back in refrigerator several hours before cooking.
This can be stored in the refrigerator for several days (or in freezer in an airtight container for several months) before cooking.

title: janssons frestelse(jansson's temptation)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut them into thin strips.
Peel and thinly slice onions.
Brown the onions and potatoes in a little butter. Alternate layers of potatoes/onions with anchovies or pickled sardelles in a buttered, ovenproof dish.
The top layer should be potatoes.
Pour 1/3 cup plus 3 tablespoons thick cream over the dish.
You can mix the cream with some of the liquid in the tin if you like.
Sprinkle some bread crumbs over.
Dot with 1 to 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in a 400° oven for approximately 40 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup plus 3 tablespoons thick cream.
Continue to bake for another 10 minutes until the potatoes are soft.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cool lime pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin, sugar and water in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Add lime rind and juice.
Pour into bowl and cover with plastic wrap and chill until cold and slightly thickened.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and lime slices, if desired.

title: broiled "zesty oysters"
directions: Open the oysters, leaving oyster in the deep half of the shell; discard other shell.
Arrange oysters, single layer, on a baking pan.
On every oyster, put 1 drop Worcestershire sauce. (This sauce may be omitted by ginger lovers).
A pinch of ginger and a few crumbs of bacon is sprinkled on each oyster.
Sprinkle over all with paprika.
Broil about 4 inches from the flame until edge of oysters curl and bacon is done, just 3 to 4 minutes. Serve with lemon or lime wedges; add a colorful flower and leaf on the tray.
Serves two to four persons.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef; drain and set aside.
Bring 8 cups hot water to boiling.
Add pasta.
Reduce heat.
Cook in gently boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Return to pan. Halve pepperoni and add to pasta.
Add ground beef.
Stir in pizza sauce, 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan.
Transfer to a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until hot.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayo.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels. Combine with cheeses, salad dressing and olives. Lightly grease or spray regular muffin tin and press 1 wonton wrapper in each cup. Brush with oil or spray.
Bake 5 minutes until golden brown. Remove from tins; place on baking sheet.
After all wraps are cooked, fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: dates bread
directions: Set stove at 373°; beat flour with eggs, margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add dates, raisins and nuts one at a time; beat altogether until smooth.
Place in a 6 x 3-inch pan, then place in oven for 45 minutes, then add brown sugar and serve.

title: chatters(makes 64)
directions: Let butter and cheese soften.
Mix with mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crab.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze for 10 minutes, then broil until bubbly.
Cut into quarters, like pie slices.
May be made and frozen a couple weeks in advance.
No thawing necessary.

title: holcombe's "famous" chocolate chip hotcakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chocolate chips.
After pouring each hotcake onto a hot griddle, drop 5 chocolate chips into each.
Flip and finish cooking.
Best served with butter and a sprinkle of powdered sugar.

title: coney dog sauce
directions: Combine onion, rice, pepper and 4 quarts water in a large roaster.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Add raw ground beef and bake 50 minutes more.
Drain off excess fat; add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour more.

title: ham wrap ups
directions: Put cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard and olives in blender. Puree until smooth.
Spread thinly on ham slices; roll each as for jelly roll.
Wrap in foil and chill several hours.
Slice in 1/4 slice.
Serve on crackers.

title: butterscotch bits (cookies)
directions: Melt butterscotch bits over hot water.
When melted and hot, throw in noodles and nuts and stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: favorite cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature. Chop green onions, adding some of the green part. Chop ham. Mix into cream cheese. Add other ingredients. Mix well. Shape into ball; roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate before serving.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Blend in enough milk until frosting is of spreading consistency.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When thick, take off heat and wait 5 minutes, then fold in 1/2 jar of Miracle Whip.
Beat well.

title: snack bars
directions: Mix together in double boiler until all is melted, except cereal.
Mix in the Special K cereal into large bowl.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: party snack mix
directions: Combine all together.
Store in lightly covered container. Serve as a snack.
Makes about 10 cups mix.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with melted butter.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan. Pour and spread Eagle Brand milk over cracker crumb crust.
Top with chocolate chips, then coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 25 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until brown; remove garlic.
Cook and stir rice in oil until golden, about 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth and salsa.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes (do not lift cover or stir).

title: rob's tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Add soup (undiluted) and tuna and mix well.
Add enough milk to make creamy.
Pour into casserole dish and
spread potato chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza rice salad
directions: Mix all together with half of the dressing.
Chill and just before serving, add remaining dressing.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden.
Cut meat into small, narrow strips, 1 1/2 inches long.
Mix meat with onions.
Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Add mushrooms; cut into quarters, if large.
Add seasoning, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce. Simmer until meat is tender (about 15 minutes before serving, stir in sour cream).
Serve with Pilaf.

title: sauteed salmon
directions: Pour half the oil into a large skillet to coat bottom.
Place salmon in pan.
Pour remaining oil over top and add onion, olives and pepper.
Saute about 15 minutes, covered.
Serve alongside boiled potatoes, yucca or rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Put into 2 well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: george washington gingerbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients (except soda).
Add eggs, molasses and shortening.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Add slowly to other ingredients.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sole fillet meuniere
directions: Dry the sole
fillets
and dip in seasoned flour.
In a large skillet heat
the
2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon oil (add more
if
necessary) until butter has foamed and foam begins to subside.
Add
the	fillets carefully and cook for a total of 10 minutes per inch, cooking half of the time on each side.
Remove to	a
warm
serving
dish	to
keep
warm.
The cooking should be done
on
a medium to high heat, taking care that the sole	does not
burn, but browns nicely.
Remove any little bits of flour
or fish
from
the
pan
with a slotted spoon.
Add the 2
to
4 tablespoons
of butter and cook over medium to high heat
until the
butter
foams up and the foam subsides and the butter	colors to
a light brown. Do not let the butter burn.
All
at
once add the remaining ingredients, swirl around the pan and then pour the foaming liquid over the fish. Serve at once.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and prepare rind and all.
Do not peel.
Grind all ingredients.
Sweeten to taste.
Good with holiday meals.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put soup, tuna, milk and peas in a saucepan; let it come to a boil.
Crumble potato chips in bottom of a baking dish.
Add egg noodles and tuna mixture on top of chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream together butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla, water and eggs.
Combine butter/egg mixture with the dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in preheated 375° oven.
Cool on wire racks. Makes 50 to 60.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 3-quart glass ceramic casserole dish, combine water and butter.
Heat at High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in sugar and molasses.
Heat at High 13 to 14 minutes or until mixture reads 300° when tested with candy thermometer.
Quickly stir in peanuts and baking soda; stir until soda foams.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin.
To complete, let stand until candy is hardened; break into small pieces.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 3/4 cup boiling water.
Pour 1/4 cup boiling water over cranberries and strawberries.
Stir to break up.
Add all other ingredients and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: scalloped summer squash(yields 5 servings)
directions: Heat butter.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper; cook.
Cut squash in cubes.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook until tender.

title: baked corn
directions: Thaw frozen corn; drain canned corn.
Mix with mixer, flour, sugar, salt, eggs, milk and butter.
Add corn and baking powder. Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until light brown and set. Serve hot.

title: party punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Float ice cream and orange sherbet on top.
Good idea to chill juices overnight.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Let potatoes (hash browns) thaw.
Layer in baking dish in this order:

hash browns, salt and pepper lightly, 1/2 cup butter, melted, soup (undiluted), cheese (you can substitute grated cheese), sour cream, onion (chopped or sliced thin) and corn flakes (you can use potato chips or bread crumbs).
Sprinkle lightly with butter. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add water to equal one gallon and chill.
Easy to make and tastes great.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cook raisins, water, sugar and flour until thick.
Stir in the vanilla and the vinegar.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie crust and cool. Cook pudding according to package directions.
Pour cooked pudding into cooled pie crust. Mix jello and 1 cup hot water.
Add 1/2 cup ice water. Stir in the strawberries. Set until still stirable.
Pour over pudding mixture.
May be served with whipped cream.
Sugar-free jello and pudding works fine with this recipe.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer lettuce, beans, cheese, onions and tomatoes.
Last, take bag of crushed Fritos and put on top.
Drizzle green onion dressing over top of all ingredients.

title: diet pineapple orange pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup Faygo.
Put 1/2 cup Faygo in blender with cottage cheese, sweetener, vanilla and lemon juice. Blend until creamy.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Blend in gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until thick.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Prepare chicken stock.
Saute onions in butter until translucent.
Add flour; mix thoroughly.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Slowly add hot chicken stock, stirring until smooth.
Add half and half and remaining spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add potatoes; stir.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese, bacon bits and chives.

title: sweet and sour meatballs with vidalia onions
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients until well blended.
Shape into walnut sized balls.
Broil in oven for a few minutes.
Put into prepared sauce.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: breakfast grits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
When bubbling, take off heat.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Bake in greased dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as if going to mash. Combine ingredients, except parsley and paprika. This will be very creamy. Pour in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Top with parsley flakes and paprika after baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except peanut butter.
Cook until syrup is a soft ball when dropped in cold water, approximately 15 or 20 minutes.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Saute onion.
Add milk and dissolve flour in milk as it warms. Add seasonings, butter, chicken bouillon cubes, etc.
Bring to a low boil (keep stirring), add crab meat and cook for 5 minutes, (watch so crab meat does not burn on bottom) at a low boil.
Cool and serve.

title: "lazy day" chicken
directions: Place chicken in 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole.
Cover with blended soups.
Sprinkle well with cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Uncover and bake 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put sliced apples in greased pan.
Mix together all ingredients and place on top of apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender (about 25 to 30 minutes).

title: toot-toot hot bean dish
directions: Brown
bacon
in frying pan.
Remove
bacon
and
brown hamburger and onion in bacon grease.
Put all ingredients in a casserole and mix.	Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and mash sweet potato while hot.
Add sugar.
Stir.
Add beaten eggs, melted oleo or margarine, salt and spices and fold in evaporated milk, chilled and whipped.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine carrots, pepper and onion in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix thoroughly soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and salt; mix into vegetables.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 8 hours.

title: noodle stroganoff
directions: Combine hamburger, bread, eggs, salt, pepper and onion.
Make into small balls.
Fry until brown; pour off grease.
Mix soups, sour cream and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Let simmer.
Cook noodles as directed until done; drain, then mix together.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth to simmering.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, cornstarch and garlic and let simmer.
When ready to serve, beat egg and slowly drizzle into soup.
Let simmer 1 minute more.

title: jonny cakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Gradually add water, stirring to form soft dough. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, about 1 minute. Cut or pat dough into 3-inch rounds, about 1/2-inch thick. Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat. Add cakes and fry 10 minutes or until golden brown, turning occasionally. Split cakes in half and spread with butter or a slice of American cheese.

title: citrus sparkle
directions: Combine water and sugar in blender; cover and blend until sugar is dissolved.
Add oranges, lemon, limes and pineapple.
Cover and blend until liquified.
Pour 1/2 cup into glass.
Add a few ice cubes and fill with carbonated water.

title: savory hearty beef soup
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bowl and eat.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, onion, salt, honey and 2 tablespoons vinegar in blender.
Add oil (small amount at a time), blending constantly.
When all has been added and mixture is thick, add poppy seed and remaining 3 tablespoons vinegar.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute together the pepper, onion, celery and hamburg in large frying pan.
Transfer to large pot and add tomato sauce, paste and prepared sauces.
Add the rest of dry ingredients.
Simmer one hour, covered, stirring occasionally.
Prepared meatballs may also be added.

title: guacamole salad
directions: In a blender container, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smoother, scraping down sides of container as necessary.
Place in a serving bowl.
Cover and chill before serving.
Serve as a dip with fresh vegetables.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: scotch cake
directions: Place flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, put oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over sugar and flour; mix well.
Add and mix well the buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: easiest ever appetizers
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: lu's hamburg-chili bake
directions: Crumble beef into heated skillet. Add onion. Drain grease. Combine soup, evaporated milk and chilies. Mix until smooth. Combine beef and soup mixtures. Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan with half of the tortilla quarters. Spoon half the hamburg mixture over tortillas. Arrange remaining tortillas on top. Spoon rest of hamburg. Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mama lindy's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add alternately with milk, flour, baking powder, salt, coconut flavor and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured pan in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, and margarine, beat well. Add syrup and vanilla mix well. Pour into pie shell and then put pecans in by hand. Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour until brown.

title: hearty beef "n" cheese crescent pie
directions: In a large frying pan, brown beef, onion and green pepper. Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, green beans, garlic salt and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine and boil oleo, Wesson oil and water. Add sugar, flour and salt. Mix hot and dry ingredients, then add cocoa, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Pour in greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick creamed eggs
directions: Empty soup into a small saucepan.
Add sour cream and pimiento and mix until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it is good and hot.
Take off heat and add sliced eggs and salt and pepper, too.
Serve over rice or squares of corn bread.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, scant cup sugar, whipped cream and spread on top of first layer.

title: pineapple-green onion cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape in ball.
Roll in crushed pretzels.

title: potato patties
directions: Mix well; shape into 6 patties.
Dip in flour, then brown slowly in butter, about 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, vegetable oil, sugar and brown sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, vanilla and soda; mix well, then add salt, pudding and flour.
Mix until thick.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350°.
Bake according to size.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix soup and mayonnaise.
Mix in all vegetables.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar in a bowl.
Blend in butter or margarine until a soft dough is formed.
If dough is too soft to handle, cover and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Roll in the coconut.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lemon layer angel food
directions: Mix, bake and cool cake as directed on label. Slice cake into 3 layers. Cook pudding according to package directions for pie filling. Spread pudding between layers and on top of the cake. Prepare whipped topping according to directions. Spread on sides of cake. Chill for at least 3 hours before serving to allow pudding to set. Store in refrigerator. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: easy bake pizza
directions: Preheat the oven to 375° and grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a skillet, brown the sausage over medium low heat; while the meat is browning, dice up the green pepper, onion or your choice of ingredients.
Add the sauce and your pizza ingredients (onions, peppers, etc.) to the skillet; cook for about 5 minutes.
Turn off heat; set aside.

On a cutting board, lay out your raw biscuit dough and cut each piece in 1/2. Take 1/2 of your batch and cut up biscuits and layer in the bottom of your baking dish (bottom won't be covered, rolls will expand while cooking).
Layer over the biscuits 1/2 of the sauce mixture, then add 1 cup of the cheese. Place another layer of biscuits over this.
Layer with the sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 425°.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Peel carrots and cut in diagonal strips.
Put carrots in bottom of crock-pot.
Add 1 can drained mushrooms to carrots. Pour 1 cup of water over vegetables.
Next add chicken.
Sprinkle soups over chicken.
Cook in covered crock-pot on low power for 10 hours or until chicken is tender.
For a complete meal, serve with wild rice.
Cook wild rice according to instructions on box.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil until tender; drain and set aside.
Make a gravy with flour, water and Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour gravy over meat seasoned with garlic salt and other seasonings.
When gravy thickens, put potatoes in and simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli, bacon, onion and peanuts; then toss well.

title: jennifer's quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell or a casserole sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until center set.

title: stuffed mushroom appetizers
directions: Wash mushrooms and gently twist to pull out stems making a cavity in each mushroom cap.
Dip each mushroom in melted butter or bacon grease.
Mix remaining ingredients and stuff each cap fully.
Place small pieces of Swiss cheese or Brick cheese on top of each mushroom cap.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Combine all ingredients well and put in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Stir gently once or twice during the cooking.
Serve hot.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Stir flour and sugar together.
Add soda to pineapple; work quickly as it foams.
Add eggs and pineapple and stir together. Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Add enough milk to flour to make a smooth, thin paste.
Add eggs and salt to paste.
Beat.
Heat remaining milk and sugar until almost scalding; stir in paste mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Cool; fold in vanilla.
Add cream (whipped) and Grape-Nuts just before serving.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage, onion and green pepper with 1/2 cup sugar. Let stand.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper, salt, dry mustard and celery seed.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate, covered.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put the sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and salt in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat and stir in the rolled oats, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper to make 48 cookies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Pour in entire bottle of salad dressing.
Let sit in fridge overnight.
Then add Salad Supreme and fresh vegetables (olives, carrots, onions and green peppers).
It works best if mixed with your hands.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and bananas, beating until light. Alternately add flour mixture and milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap.
Stores or freezes well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs; mix.
Add carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Turn into greased and floured long pan or spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: decadent potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (not peeled) until nearly done.
While potatoes are cooking, chop bacon and saute with onion.
When potatoes are nearly done, drain water and chop into large chunks.
Put potatoes into skillet with bacon.
Add parsley and seasoning.
Cook another 5 minutes and serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well; for each cup of water, add 3 heaping teaspoonfuls of mixture.

title: zucchini cake(a favorite of adam and christopher and easy to make!)
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add raisins, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Ice with a Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: freezer stuffed pepper
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, cooked rice, Cheez Whiz, salt and pepper.
Put in green peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely, package, place in refrigerator overnight, then put in freezer.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles until half done.
Cook broccoli.
Combine butter, half and half, cream, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add broccoli and noodles.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 to 25 minutes until starts to thicken.
Add cheese to complete thickening.
Serve immediately.

title: summer quick sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, Good Seasons dressing, all spices and a little water.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add grated cheese.
Serve.

title: bubbles
directions: Combine ingredients into an unbreakable bottle.
Use fly swatters, strawberry baskets, plastic colander or spoons with holes for lots of out door bubbles.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: crock-pot lentil soup
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot.
Fill crock-pot 2/3 full with water.
Cook on low for at least 5 hours.
When finished, cook 1/2 cup tubettini macaroni or other small macaroni separately, then add to crock-pot.
Serve with Romano cheese sprinkled on top and crusty French bread.

title: spinach chicken breasts
directions: In a medium skillet melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
Add shallots and cook 5 minutes or until soft.
Remove from heat.
Squeeze spinach to remove excess moisture.
Add to skillet with salt, pepper and nutmeg; stir to mix.
Spoon into a medium bowl.
Add cheese and stir until well mixed.
Cover and chill until mixture holds shape.
(Shape into 8 equal portions.)

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle paprika on beef; brown in butter.
Add broth and garlic; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add green peppers and onions.
Cook for 5 minutes more.
Combine water, soy sauce and cornstarch; add to pan and cook, stirring constantly for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add the rest.
Bake in long pan 30 or 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pralines
directions: Cook to a soft ball and add 1 cup nuts.
Beat by hand until it can be dropped on greased paper.
(This hardens too fast for an electric mixer.)
I usually set it in a pan of cool water while beating to help it cool.

title: velveeta hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until heated through.

title: people chow
directions: Melt the peanut butter and chocolate chips with oil in microwave.
Add 1 box of Crispix cereal.
Pour in sealed container and shake.
Dump sugar in container and seal, then shake.

title: lo-cal coating for fish and chicken
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Coat fish fillets with coating mixture. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
You will think it has been fried.

title: stir-fried pork and vegetables
directions: In medium bowl, mix well first 5 ingredients; add pork and toss lightly to coat.
In 5-quart Dutch oven or 12-inch skillet over high heat in 1/4 cup hot oil, cook broccoli, mushrooms and salt, stirring quickly (like stir-fry) until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Place vegetables and liquid on heated platter; keep warm.
In same Dutch oven over high heat, heat 6 more tablespoons oil until very hot.
Add meat mixture and stir-fry until meat loses pink color, about 2 minutes.
Return vegetables to Dutch oven; stir-fry until heated through.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican dish ole'
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream; put in long casserole.
Layer all other ingredients on top; serve with round chips.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine cooked ground
beef, beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, water and the chili con carne.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Put a layer of chips in a long pan.
Pour half of mixture over chips. Add half the cheese on top.
Add another layer of chips.
Put remaining mixture on top.
Layer the onion, then add the rest of the cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until the cheese is melted.

title: delicious eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant crosswise about 1/2-inch thick.
Soak slices to cover in cold salted water for 20 minutes; drain well.
Spread each slice generously with mayonnaise and top with lots of chopped onions.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle each slice with Parmesan cheese. Broil until golden.

title: country salad
directions: In you plate, crumble cornbread.
Top with bacon and salad mixtures.
Pour hot grease over and mix.
Next all cottage cheese and buttermilk to taste.
Mix again and enjoy!

title: alison's buried cherry cookies
directions: Drain cherries and reserve juice.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a dent in the center and place cherry in dent.
Spoon 1 teaspoon frosting to cover cherry.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and cheese together and add cream of celery soup, add broccoli.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.
Let cool.
Mix well, cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread onto cooled pretzel crust.
Mix together, the Jell-O, boiling water and strawberries.
Stir until thawed and thickened.
Pour over cream cheese layer and refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 16, depending on the size of serving.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to box.
Combine grits in baking dish with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Cool 30 minutes before serving.
This is great with pork roast with Anaheim peppers layered on top to bake flavor in.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Mix cheese and flour together.
Add baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat egg with milk and melted butter.
Stir into flour mixture.
Spoon into muffin pans (use nonstick pans if possible). I also like them better cooked as small muffins.
Bake at 350°.

title: onion soup
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, place butter and onions; cover. Microwave at High for 18 to 20 minutes or until tender, stirring 2 times.
Add consomme, hot water, wine, Worcestershire and pepper; re-cover.
Microwave at High for 8 to 9 minutes or until boiling. Divide among 4 individual 15-ounce casseroles or soup bowls.
Top each casserole with 2 slices of French bread.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of Swiss cheese and 1 teaspoon of Parmesan cheese over the bread in each casserole.
Arrange in a circle in the oven and microwave at Medium for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: super peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in ice cream churn.

title: richmond coconut-black walnut cake
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil, and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, coconut, and flavoring.

title: mayonnaise dressing(for macaroni or potato salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan or double boiler.
Bring to a boil and boil until slightly thick.
Pour over potatoes or macaroni.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and cheese. Beat with mixer until combined. Saute onions in butter until soft, then add 1/3 of the onion mixture to potatoes and cheese. Cook noodles until they're not quite done. Generously butter a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place a layer of noodles, then potatoes, then noodles, etc. ending with noodles. Pour remaining onion sauce on top. Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked caramel apples
directions: Place apples in
microwave dish; sprinkle with brown sugar. Top with 2 tablespoons topping; sprinkle with pecans and rest of topping. Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 4 thin layers at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: *butterscotch sauce
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and butter together for 5 minutes, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add cream or milk; bring to boiling point again.
Add vanilla and serve hot or cold.
Especially good over ice cream.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, brown ground beef and onion; set aside. In same pan, saut carrots, celery, basil and parsley flakes in 1 tablespoon butter until veggies are tender (about 10 minutes). Add both cans of chicken broth and potatoes; add cooked hamburger. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sesame chicken wings with apricot glaze
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Mix preserves, vinegar, onion and garlic.
Mix sesame seed and crumbs in a separate bowl.
Dip chicken wings into preserve mixture, then drain and press firmly into crumb mixture.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, baking powder, sugar, Crisco and flour; mix well and knead.
Cut with biscuit cutters, dip in melted butter and fold in half.
Place on sprayed cookie sheet.
Raise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon steaks teriyaki
directions: Place steaks in shallow pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except butter.
Pour over salmon.
Let stand 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove steaks from marinade.
Brush both sides with melted butter and broil 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until browned and easily flaked.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk.
Beat egg and mix with sugar, cocoa and cornstarch or flour.
Then stir into hot milk and cook until thick on medium heat.
Add butter, vanilla and salt.
Then pour in pie crust (baked).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add well beaten eggs. Mix in peanut butter well.
Add all dry ingredients.
Sift before adding.
Dough will be stiff.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
