Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jackie's lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and 1 egg together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "baked" can beans
directions: Place all ingredients in bean pot; mix well.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve warm.
Serve with broccoli, artichokes, asparagus, etc.

title: rice babka with apples
directions: In large bowl, mix the rice, melted butter, sugar, slightly beaten egg yolks, raisins and vanilla.
Grate apples on coarse grater or finely chop.
Add the apples to the rice mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into rice.
Grease generously a 3-quart casserole or a pan with a wide bottom of that size. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Put the rice into the pan, even out. Sprinkle with sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with sour cream, if desired.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip cream cheese, then add sugar and mayonnaise.
Add cranberry sauce and whip more.
Fold in pineapple and nuts, then whipped cream last.
Freeze.
(I freeze mine in baking cups in a muffin tin.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apple slices in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Beat margarine.
Mix in sugar, flour and cinnamon. Stir in cereal.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk to egg, then add shortening.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn into well greased 6 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apple raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix bran cereal, yogurt, milk, margarine and eggs together. Let stand 5 minutes in a bowl.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in bran mixture, just until blended.
Stir in apples and raisins.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Dissolve coffee in hot water.
Combine egg whites, brown sugar and cream of tartar in top of double boiler.
Beat with mixer until frosting forms stiff peaks (5 to 7 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Beat in vanilla.
Ice the cake.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and add milk, but leave it thick.
Spoon out in deep, hot grease.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Combine noodles, almonds and seed.
Saute in 1 stick margarine until brown.

title: minestrone beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large pan.
Add the next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Sprinkle rice into the mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve as a main dish topped with shredded cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: favorite `beef' loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Shape mixture (juicy) in loaf in shallow baking dish.
(I use bread pans.)
Press 2 green pepper rings and onion rings atop meat loaf, if desired.
Bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve the first 4 ingredients and let cool.
Put yeast in warm water.
Then add eggs, shortening mix and yeast when it cools. Beat in flour and oats.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in well-greased bowl. Cover; let rise in warm place free of drafts for 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Let set 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour in 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: boiled cookies(serves 16 to 20)
directions: Stir and bring first 4 ingredients to a high boil.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Add vanilla, and mix it together.
Lay them on wax paper as large as desired.

title: cheesy puffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients. Beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Fill 12 greased medium muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: easy party punch
directions: Make coffee double strength.
Sweeten slightly with powdered sugar.
Freeze mixture to a mush, stirring frequently.
Serve in a frosty sherbet cup.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper in oil.
Add all remaining
ingredients,
except cheese and noodles.
Cook slowly for
hour.
Add	cooked,
drained noodles.
Put in a large baking
dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Makes about 10 servings.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Spread evenly in bottom of dish or pan.
Mix the strawberries with glaze.
Spread over cake. Mix the sour cream, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar together; spread over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Quick and easy dessert.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Cook until a little forms a hard ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites stiff and don't pour syrup over egg whites until you let it cool for a minute, then beat the mixture until very stiff.
Pour out on a board covered with powdered sugar.
Pat out with palm or hand and spread with as much peanut butter as you like.
Roll up and slice.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Put sugar, raisins, shortening, cinnamon and hot water on stove and cook for about 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, add soda and flour.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange slice candy
directions: Mix all ingredients and work together with your hands until sticky.
Divide dough into four parts. Form logs with the dough and roll each log in powdered sugar until covered.
Cover the rolls with waxed paper and refrigerate one day.
Cut into slices to serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and the butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° and cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and
Cool Whip and pour over the pretzel crumbs.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot pineapple juice.
Add strawberries.
Let partially congeal (30 to 35 minutes) and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate bark and stir in Rice Krispies.
Spread thinly over pizza pan.
Let cool.
Sprinkle pecans over top and put M&M's on.
Melt white bark and drizzle over top.
You may separate white bark into 2 or 3 containers and put food coloring in it for a more colorful pizza.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or in the microwave for approximately 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball; roll in nuts and chill.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
Mix liquid ingredients in another.
Combine the two.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sugarplum cookies
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, blend shortening, granulated
sugar, egg, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla on low
speed.
(Two to 3 tablespoons of milk may be added if necessary).
Using
level
teaspoonful
of
dough for each, shape
into
ball around a cherry piece.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool. Dip top
of each cookie into glaze.
Roll cookie in decorator sugar. Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water in small saucepan; cool. Stir in flour; mix until smooth.
Add cream and salt.
Cook until thickened.
Wash and slice mushrooms into a 2-quart casserole. Pour sauce over mushrooms.
Mix crumbs with cheese and sprinkle over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Great with roast beef!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
After done, spoon Cheez Whiz on top as desired.

title: wild gooey bluey
directions: Blend butter, flour, 1 1/2 cups of brown sugar and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients with 6 cups brown sugar.
Pour over hot crust and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into squares to serve.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and sugar together.
Knead mixture like bread dough.
Form mixture into balls buckeye size. Place balls on tray lined with wax paper, chill.

title: crisp cinnamon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, cream together shortening and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add 1/2 of flour mixture, then the milk and then remaining flour mixture.
Mix well.
Form teaspoons of dough into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet, then flatten into a 1/8-inch thick circle.
Bake for 10 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a skillet, saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in tomato sauce, water, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add more water if needed.
Add thawed shrimp.
Bring mixture to a boil. Cook, covered, over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Serve Shrimp Creole over fluffy rice (your own recipe).
This recipe is for 2 generous servings.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Saute chicken in butter and seasoning.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Stir well.
Add water to desired thickness.
Add cooked noodles.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into wedges.
Mix dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Add potatoes and shake well.
Put wedges on cookie sheet.
Melt butter and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: brunch-in-a-dish
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Layer potatoes and sausage in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers. Sprinkle over cheese. Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more until set. Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix the eggs, pineapple and vanilla together.
Fold together.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts.
Flatten with heel of hand. Wrap a slice of ham around a piece of cheese about 2 x 1/4-inch. Then wrap chicken around ham and cheese.
This may be secured with a toothpick.
Dip chicken in flour, then in egg wash (egg in milk) and then in crumbs.
Brown in hot oil for 4 minutes per side.
To finish in microwave, place meat on a platter set in oven on roast or medium setting for 1 1/2 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Reserve peach juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup peach juice and set aside.
Heat remaining juice, brown sugar, cinnamon, cranberry sauce and butter.
When butter melts, add cornstarch mixture.
Stir over medium heat until thickened. Add yams, cover and cook 10 minutes. Stir in peaches.
Heat through.

title: quick sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork in 1-inch cubes.
In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add pork, 1/3 at a time.
Brown.
Add pineapple, corn syrup, vinegar, catsup, soy sauce and garlic. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes or until pork is tender.
Add green pepper.
Mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Add to skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef in 5-quart pot.
Drain off grease.
Add onion, catsup and chili powder to taste.
Bring to boil on high, then turn heat down to low and let simmer at least 2 hours.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in a bag and add chicken that is cut in small pieces and coat.
Put oil in a deep frypan and brown chicken.
Add about 1/3 cup of water, then add the bag of Pasta Accents and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Cook California Blend until tender.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Mix all together.
Cook on low until cheese melts.

title: tortillas
directions: Beat eggs and salt together; add cornmeal and mix well. Combine the cornstarch and milk to form a smooth batter.
Add the egg mixture to this and mix again until smooth.
Add the oil or melted oleo, stirring constantly.
Grease a 7-inch skillet and heat it.
Pour a small amount of the batter on the bottom of the skillet, tilting the pan and making sure the batter covers the bottom evenly.
When brown on one side, flip over and brown the other. Tortillas should be almost paper thin.
If used for tacos, fold tortillas over while warm to make taco shell.

title: crunchy zucchini bars
directions: Mix together as for pie crust the flour, 2 cups sugar, oleo and salt.
Pat 1/2 of the mixture in the bottom of a 10 x 15-inch ungreased pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Completely soften dry beans by covering beans with 3 times their volume of unsalted water and boil 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Discard water after boiling.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot; stir.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or on high 5 to 6 hours.

title: a dynamite crowd-pleaser(beverage)
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except for the ginger ale.
Just before serving, slowly pour in the ginger ale.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Stir over medium heat until heated through.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If too thick, add a little milk.

title: c.a.'s special chicken dip
directions: Place all ingredients, except oil, in a food processor.
Blend ingredients well.
Slowly add oil, a few drops at a time.
Blend until all ingredients have been completely emulsified.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix together; bake in 350° oven.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix sugar, salt, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed in boiler with squash and peppers mix.
Boil 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: lazy man's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Form into patties and fry in pan with thin layer of oil in bottom over medium-high heat.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs and let stand 1 hour.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Add to bread crumbs and milk with melted butter. Flavor with vanilla.
Mix in coconut and raisins.
Bake in moderate 350°
oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with sauce.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender and pick off of bone.
Mix everything together except biscuits.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400°, then put biscuits on top and bake until all is done and biscuits are brown.

title: bean soup
directions: Pour chicken stock in pan.
Add chicken, onion, celery, garlic, parsley, rosemary, basil, thyme, oregano, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 45 minutes.
Place sausage in skillet.
Cover with water and simmer 15 minutes. Drain sausage, remove skin and cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Add slices of sausage and ham to soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 10 minutes.
(If you use cooked chicken you can cut the first cooking time to 30 minutes, instead of 45 minutes.)

title: speedy baked beans
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until bubbly. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from all fruit.
Use fruit juice instead of milk in pudding.
Put Tang in with vanilla pudding.
Mix all together.

title: turkey melt sandwich
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Spread mixture over toasted bread.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet; top with cheese.
Broil 4 inches from heat for approximately 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon only just until all is mixed well. Bake in square pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion and peas.
Spread mayonnaise evenly on top of ingredients, then sprinkle grated cheese and bacon bits over the top of mayonnaise.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: california carrots
directions: Pare carrots, cut diagonally in thin slices, combine with raisins, water and salt in medium saucepan. Cover and heat to boiling, then simmer 30 minutes or until carrots are done. Drain, sprinkle with brown sugar, add butter and lemon juice. Heat slowly until butter melts, then cook, stirring often, 10 minutes or until carrots are richly glazed.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water; add milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and margarine.
Cool slightly.
Slice 2 bananas.
Dip in lemon juice and layer in pie shell.
Pour filling over bananas and cover.
Chill 4 hours.
Slice remaining banana and use to garnish top of pie.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with enough salad dressing to hold together.

title: cherry cola mold
directions: Blend very soft cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir into cheese mixture, blending well.
Drain cherries and pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Add syrup and cola to jello mixture. Chill until quite thick.
Fold in cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Place in mold and chill.

title: cabbage noodle skillet
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet on high heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent and tender.
Add cabbage; reduce heat to medium and cook until cabbage has softened.
Add cooked noodles, salt and caraway seed, turning often with spatula, to prevent scorching.
Cook until mixture is browned.

title: sandy's punch
directions: Combine all and serve at once.
Looks nice with an ice ring; use ginger ale or fruit juice, salt and combination of fruits.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt
oleo
in	casserole
dish and pour out for later. Pour 1/2
of
the
stuffing mix into buttered casserole dish. Mix squash,
soup,
sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour this over the
stuffing mix and top with the remaining half of the stuffing mix.
Pour
melted
oleo over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rolled chicken breast
directions: Pound chicken pieces with mallet working from center out to about 1/4 inch thick. Sprinkle with salt. Place ham slice and cheese stick on each cutlet. Tuck in sides and roll. Skewer or tie with string. Coat rolls with flour. Brown in skillet with butter and set aside in a baking dish. In same skillet, combine 1/2 cup water, gravy base, and mushrooms. Heat, stir and incorporate any crusty chicken bits in skillet. Pour mix over chicken, cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until tender. Transfer chicken to warm platter. Add to remaining gravy by blending 2 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup cold water. Cook and stir until thickened. Pour over chicken, garnish with toasted almonds.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add mashed bananas and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake 45 minutes at 350° in loaf pan.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and vanilla plus 1/2 cup mashed blueberries.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining blueberries.
Bake in muffin tins lined with papers. Fill 3/4 full; sprinkle a little sugar and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and Italian dressing.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Pour over potatoes.
Add celery, eggs and relish.
Toss lightly.
Chill several hours.

title: microwave pineapple crisp
directions: Stir together rolled oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Place pineapple in a 10 ounce casserole dish.
Sprinkle the rolled oats mixture over the pineapple.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes or until the pineapple is hot.
Rotate dish 1/4 of a turn every minute.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 1 to 2 servings.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized portions.
Arrange in a covered pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split surprise
directions: Mix ingredients and press into a 9 X 13 pan.
Put in the refrigerator for 15 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients well, pour into a greased casserole dish, do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: herbed baked pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in egg with 2 tablespoons of milk.
Coat with crushed stuffing.
Brown.
Put in greased casserole and pour over the chops the mushroom soup, mixed with the sherry and dry mustard. Cover and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mango chutney
directions: Peel and cut mangos in pieces.
Cook sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Add garlic, ginger, onion, salt, raisins, peppers and spices.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add mangos and cook until transparent.

title: sangria punch
directions: Strain juices; add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Just before serving mix juice mixture and wine in a pitcher.
Add ice. Serve in punch cups.

title: homemade chocolate gravy
directions: Boil until turns to syrup.
Pour over homemade biscuits.

title: pepperoni cheese ball
directions: Beat all ingredients (except pepperoni) until fluffy.
Blend in pepperoni.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and stir in water, not too thick.
Cook until brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients, except for the chocolate chips and nuts, for 9 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in chips until all are dissolved.
Pour into buttered plates and let cool.
If you desire pecans, pour them in with the chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly except catsup.
Shape into 2 loaves in a shallow baking pan.
Spread with catsup halfway through cooking.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and baking soda.
Using pastry cutter, food processor or 2 knives, cut 10 tablespoons of butter into flour mixture until mixture resembles coarse meal. Refrigerate.
Line a 10-inch pie plate with pie crust; crimp edges.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix molasses and water; pour 1/3 of mixture into pie crust.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of flour mixture. Repeat this process, alternating layers, ending with flour mixture.
Dot top with remaining butter.
Bake for 50 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 16 servings.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry and liquid ingredients separately, then combine thoroughly. Spread on 2 greased cookie sheets (does not need to be spread to edges of pans).
Bake 1 hour at 250° until dry and golden. Cool; break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and serve with veggies or crackers.

title: uncooked candy
directions: Work the flour into the egg white until stiff enough to knead with your hands.
Flavor and work until perfectly smooth.
Add coloring.
Form into small patties and top patty with walnut meat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and ground cloves together.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Fold in carrots and nutmeats.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions into fine pieces.
Chop or shred dried beef. Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil.
Add vegetables and chicken broth and simmer until done.

title: danish salad
directions: Mix in a large salad bowl.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and bread crumbs.
Add seasonings.
Knead meat into this mixture, using a teaspoon as a measure.
Roll balls between palms of hands and then into a dish of bread crumbs.
Let stand at least 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute celery, green onions, parsley, bell pepper and okra in butter and water, until tender. Add tomatoes, tomato juice, soup, mushrooms, rice and shrimp. Stir and simmer until well blended. Add spices and simmer 5 minutes more.

title: fried noodles (german)
directions: Use any noodle recipe, cut noodles in larger pieces than usual, put into boiling water, cook until done.
Put on a griddle or in a frying pan with a small amount of grease, fry until brown. Break an egg over them (number depends on how many noodles you make).

title: oven stew
directions: Spread meat in large roasting pan.
Add celery, carrots, onions and potatoes.
Add tomatoes with juice.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and water with corn.
Stir.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions; drain and set aside. In large skillet, cook sausage.
Remove from skillet and drain fat (reserve 1 tablespoon).
Cook green onions and garlic in it.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine cooked pasta, sausage, onion, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce, half of Mozzarella, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Bake, covered in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake for 5 to 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Puree/blend in blender the first 5 ingredients.
Cook 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook all together for 1 hour.
Put in hot jars.
Remove bay leaves after cooking.
Process 20 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: boneless chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish and cover with cheese. Pour broccoli soup on top.
Place slices of tomato on top of soup. Mix Stove Top dressing as directed and place on top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dick's dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix remaining ingredients with artichoke hearts and bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until completely heated.
Serve with white corn tostadas chips.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into 1-inch pieces.
Season with salt.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Brown spareribs in skillet; drain off fat. Pour vinegar over ribs.
Add chopped garlic; cover and steam for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sugar, Karo syrup and soy sauce; mix well. Add pineapple chunks with syrup.
Bring to boil.
Just before serving, add cornstarch, diluted in small amount of water.
Serve hot.
Serves 5.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake covered dish for 2 hours.
Add raisins.
Stir and bake uncovered for 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Deep fry 2 ounces rice sticks until lightly golden.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: In wok or large skillet heat 3 tablespoons oil.
Add eggs; cook and stir until set.
Set aside.
Add remaining oil to skillet.
Add green onions, garlic, shrimp and peas.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Stir in eggs and remaining ingredients.
Heat through; serve hot.

title: aspic salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water.
In a mixing bowl combine jello and tomato sauce, lime juice, salt, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and cloves; mix well.
Refrigerate until thickened but not solid.
Stir in celery and cauliflower along with eggs and pickles.
Refrigerate and stir occasionally to keep the ingredients from sinking.
Chill until firm.
Serve on a bed of Boston lettuce with dressing of Cool Whip and sour cream (half and half of each).
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine all ingredients except scallions and pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours.
Bake at 300°.
When almost done, add scallions.

title: lime jello delight
directions: Make sure pineapple and mandarin oranges are well drained. Mix all together with dry Jell-O.
Serves 20.

title: old-fashioned okra gumbo
directions: Saute okra and onions in melted butter until onion is clear. Add salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes or until all vegetables are fork-tender.

title: favorite sugar cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and extracts; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill for 1-2 hours.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2 inch cutters.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375 degrees for 7-9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: summer collard greens
directions: Wash greens in warm or hot water.
Chop.
Place in water; add bacon drippings, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Cook on high until tender.

title: plain pastry
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is coarse.
Work water in lightly with blender until dough hangs together in a ball.
Turn 1/2 of the pastry onto lightly floured board.
Roll in sheet 1/8-inch thick.
Fit into pie pan.
Keep remainder of dough for top crust or second crust.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and spices. Combine soup, water and milk.
In large casserole, place layer of tortillas, sauce, cheese and onion. Repeat until all are used.
Bake at 350° to melt cheese.
You may top with shredded lettuce and chopped ripe olives before serving or more onions for decoration.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook slow for 1 hour.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add drained pineapple and pecans.
Arrange in layers in a flat dish, a layer of crushed vanilla wafers, then mixture, then top with crushed vanilla wafers.
Pat down.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan. Spread coconut and nuts in bottom of pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour on top of nuts and coconut. Mix together margarine, cream cheese and sugar. Drop by spoonful on top of batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cake will be shaky but will set up. DO NOT bake longer than called for.

title: flour pot bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in milk, molasses, honey and vegetable oil.
Add salt.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, whole wheat flour and wheat germ.
Slowly add flour mixture to the liquid.
Work until the dough is easy to handle. Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and firm, about 200 times.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover with cloth; let rise in warm place until double about 1 to 3 hours.

title: quick chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Combine crushed crackers and onion soup.
Mix in plastic bag.
Shake to mix well.
Drop 2 pieces of chicken at a time in bag; shake bag to coat chicken. Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave 20 to 22 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Line salad bowl with Romaine leaves.
Into bowl tear lettuce into bite-size pieces (8 cups).
Add mushrooms.
Pour Garden Dressing over greens and toss.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels; add sugar and melt margarine.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool 1 hour.

title: slushy punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water into gallon jug.
Add lemon juice, sugar, pineapple juice and Kool-Aid.
Freeze 1/2 of mixture.
Leave the other 1/2 of mixture in gallon jug and finish filling up with water.
Chill at least 6 hours before serving so it will be slushy.
Add frozen mixture in punch bowl before serving.

title: crab dip #2
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender; add cream cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add crab and mix.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: pink champagne
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Bring to boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
In 3-quart nonmetal container, combine concentrates and sugar-water mixture; refrigerate.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and grenadine; stir gently.
Serve in champagne glasses if desired for an elegant nonalcoholic party beverage.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chicken vegetable gumbo(low-fat)
directions: In large pot with lid, heat olive oil.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
With lid on, sweat the vegetables about 5 minutes.
Add okra, mushrooms, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes.
Then add chicken and cook until chicken is heated.

title: penny's pound cake
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar, 1 cup at a time.
Beat at high speed after each cup.
Add whole eggs, one at
a
time.
Beat well after each at medium speed.
Add sour
cream;
beat well. Add soda, baking powder and salt to flour.
Add
dry
ingredients
1 cup at a time, mixing well after
each
addition.
Add flavorings.
Pour into
well-greased tube pan.
Bake
1/2 hours at 300°.
Let stand 10 minutes;
remove from pan.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Dip eggplant rounds into egg, then cornmeal.
Fry in olive oil in large skillet.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chex party mix(microwave)
directions: In small bowl, add Lawry's seasoned salt and Lea & Perrins Worcestershire sauce to melted margarine; mix well.
Pour Chex cereals, nuts and Butter Braids into large Glad-Lock zipper bag. Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside Glad-Lock zipper bag.
Seal top of bag securely.
Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents of bag into large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 9 cups.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 dozen.
